name: Home in Oakland · *4.73 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath

name: Home in Oakland · *4.90 · 2 bedrooms · 3 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Our neighborhood is walking distance to shopping and restaurants in Temescal and Rockridge. There are lots of families in the neighborhood. There is always someone walking their dog.
It is a 15 minute walk to the following BART stations--Rockridge, Ashby, MacArthur. There are bus stops toward Berkeley and Downtown Oakland two blocks away. Access to all freeways is very close. It is a 20 minute drive to San Francisco without traffic! There is plenty of street parking.
It is a short ride by bike or car to UC Berkeley, Lake Merritt, Uptown, Downtown Oakland. It is an easy drive to all of the beautiful East Bay Regional Parks.
We are only 8 blocks to the best grocery/produce store in the world--Berkeley Bowl. There are lots of farmer's markets within walking distance.
host_about:
We are both chefs. We are excited to travel to new places and enjoy the world’s food. 

We have rented many vacation apartments and have rented our house.  We treat your apartment like our own.

name: Home in Oakland · *4.95 · 2 bedrooms · 4 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Quiet residential street, within walking distance of shops in the "Dimond District" of Oakland and Dimond Park. I'm happy to help you with itinerary ideas and suggestions for sights and adventures in the region.

name: Home in Oakland · *4.65 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath
neighborhood_overview:
Millsmont is almost a secret part of Oakland known mostly to locals. It's located on the hillside to the south of Mills College. (It overlooks but is not part of East Oakland, which is further south and to the west.) You can hear the Mills College bells ring each quarter hour.

Our neighbors include a ferry boat captain, a famous Mission mural painter, digital consultants for political campaigns, and a wellness oriented chiropractor.

Almost all of the buildings on our street are single family, middle class homes ($1.1M in the Bay Area) occupied by long time residents. These include Asian, Latino, black, and white residents and families - we are the most ethnically diverse zip code in the Bay Area. You'll see them all walking dogs on the street.

There's a wonderful natural foods grocery store about 10 minutes away by car - Farmer Joe's has two locations. Further away, there are many other great purveyors - Berkeley Bowl and Rockridge Market Hall.
host_about:
I am a writer, content strategist and former documentary filmmaker. Easy going, movie loving, connoisseur of life! 

I also write about organically grown wine and can tell you everywhere to go in wine country. I'm also a former travel writer and know the Bay Area well after living here for 30+ years. 

I'm well traveled, having spent time in India (all over), Italy, Greece, England and France.

name: Home in Oakland · *4.74 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 private bath
neighborhood_overview: walking distance to Trader Joe's, Lake Merritt, and a thriving shopping and restaurant part of town, but a small neighborhood feeling at home with plenty of street parking.

I'm passionate about teaching and spreading the joy of dance, especially partner dance.  I also collect rare plants and have a beautiful and interesting (if a tad unruly) garden, which I tend to all by myself, hence the unruly part.  I love to cook, but my diet is pretty basic, mostly plants, simply prepared with very little processed foods.  I'm a good conversationalist, but my schedule is erratic, so no guarantee I'll be around when you want to talk.  Happy to supply you with all the info you want about the area!  I can't live without good friends, integrity, laughter, dancing, new things to try, and nature.  When I travel, it's usually dance related, although I did achieve my dream of an English country garden tour a few years ago.   I spent the month of July in Sweden and Norway for 8 years studying a European jazz dance (boogie woogie) that I fell in love with.  My home is a quiet space, good for people who want to rest when they get back to their room, not good for people who want to party in their room, rather than on the town. (Also not good for smokers.  Please see house rules if you smoke.)

name: Rental unit in Oakland · *4.74 · Studio · 1 bed · 1 private bath

I've heard that Oakland is the second most ethnically diverse city in America... after New York City. I love that.

And while it's a diverse neighborhood, you can see from my reviews that guests feel safe here, and most of those who state that are women.

It's 0.6 miles from the nearest strip of restaurants (called "Temescal"), and about 1 mile from the nearest BART station.

I'ts 0.7 miles from The Temescal Produce Market at 5121 Telegraph Ave, Oakland.

It's 1.1 miles from Whole Foods Market at 3000 Telegraph Ave in Berkeley

It's also 1.1. miles from Berkeley Bowl at 2020 Oregon St in Berkeley. This is where I shop. It has the best prices on organic food, and a huge selection of both organic and conventional.

This area is very flat, so it's easy to bike around town
host_about: Hi I'm Trevor. I own a triplex in North Oakland and live in one unit. This is a quiet building. I'm fully vaccinated.

There are plenty of popular restaurants and cafes on College in Rockridge; Trader Joes, a bakery, and a gourmet f

name: Home in Oakland · *4.93 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath

Next to the property is a wooded park with a walking trail and playground. Within a few blocks are the most interesting stretches of Telegraph and College Avenues with excellent bakeries, cafés, restaurants, shops, and the great Temescal Farmer's Market, one of the best in the Bay.

Check out the map below and search for Rockridge on StreetAdvisor to learn more about the neighborhood.

name: Rental unit in Oakland · *4.73 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath

Take a stroll down the block to see babies and families walking along with workers, families, loiterers, commuters, homeless people, kids at play, teens on bikes, and varied and interesting houses and gardens, all enjoying the sunshine (or fog.)

Historic Oakland residential neighborhood with beautiful architecture. The Tuesday Berkeley Farmers' Market is a 3-minute walk down the street. Sweet Adeline is a superior neighborhood bakery. Guests love this delightful hidden neighborhood.

NB This is a very typical Oakland neighborhood. Guests may or may not feel comfortable walking alone late at night. Al

name: Home in Oakland · *4.93 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1.5 shared baths

A good walk (25 minutes) is up to College Avenue in the Elmwood district where you will find a movie theatre, terrific cafes and restaurants, Wells Fargo Bank, bakeries, ice cream shop, and so much more. Or walk more to the south on College Avenue to enter the Rockridge district for tons of shops and eating establishments.

host_about:

My love of baking began when I was just 4 years old and spent much of my time at my mother's side while she worked in The Vienna Bakery of Tempe, AZ.  Little did I know I would move from art and dance to baking as my life's work. 

Along with baking, I love the outdoors and am most happy when I am hiking and even happier the rare times I manage to pitch a tent somewhere beautiful; like Yosemite National Park.  My musical taste is all over the map. From straight up jazz to 60's and 70's rock to music from all over the world.

I have one daughter who has given me three super charged grandchildren, whom I just adore!  You may meet them during your stay with me.

I look forward to meeting all of you who choose to visit my home.  You will find it to be very comfortable and peaceful.  Some guests have even described it as "magical."

name: Rental unit in Oakland · *4.76 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
I have lived here in Longfellow for 23 years, and I love it. It is close to San Francisco, downtown Oakland, and downtown Berkeley. Telegraph Ave. restaurants, bars, and shops are only a short walk away. This diverse, traditionally working-class neighborhood is going through a major transformation, and currently you might find a liquor store adjacent to an upscale eatery. It is an urban neighborhood, with colorful characters. My lowest reviews are for the neighborhood-- the best fits are guests who are familiar with city environments or are open to experiencing life in the city. *Note: California's ongoing homelessness crisis impacts many Oakland neighborhoods, including this one. There are tents and RVs under most freeway overpasses, including some nearby. While I do not believe this significantly impacts safety, it can be an unpleasant experience to walk through.

Many people are here to visit San Francisco, but you could easily spend your entire vacation here in O
host_about: A native of Oberlin, OH, I've lived in CA for the last 27 years. For the past sixteen I've made the North Oakland neighborhood of Longfellow my home, and I think it's a mighty special place.  My boyfriend and I live with our three teenaged girls, two dogs, and one cat.

name: Guesthouse in Oakland · *4.97 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
host_about: I am a licensed psychotherapist in the SF Bay Area as well as Manhattan. My one bedroom garden cottage is in the rear of my private home in Oakland. Midwestern born and raised and now living bi-coastal is a dream and a goal achieved.

name: Home in Oakland · *4.90 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1.5 shared baths
neighborhood_overview:
What I love about my neighborhood: its cafes, proximity to all things Berkeley and Oakland, the weather, the architecture, arts district, music venues, bike lanes, trees, gardens, theaters, and a hundred other things.

I have lived here since 1987 and raised my daughter here. I love my neighborhood and want to share my experience with as many people as possible. A good walk (25 minutes) is up to College Avenue in the Elmwood district where you will find a movie theatre, terrific cafes and restaurants, Wells Fargo Bank, bakeries, ice cream shop, and so much more. Or walk more to the south on College Avenue to enter the Rockridge district for tons of shops and eating establishments.

Just a couple of blocks away on Adeline Street and Alcatraz Avenue are good eating places, a Yoga studio, and a few shops.
host_about:
I am the founder and president of a local bakery which I began in 1983 and from which I happily retired in January 2017.  My love of baking began when I was just 4 years old and spent much of my time at my mother's side while she worked in The Vienna Bakery of Tempe, AZ.  Little did I know I would move from art and dance to baking as my life's work. 

Along with baking, I love the outdoors and am most happy when I am hiking and even happier the rare times I manage to pitch a tent somewhere beautiful; like Yosemite National Park.  My musical taste is all over the map. From straight up jazz to 60's and 70's rock to music from all over the world.

I have one daughter who has given me three super charged grandchildren, whom I just adore!  You may meet them during your stay with me.

I look forward to meeting all of you who choose to visit my home.  You will find it to be very comfortable and peaceful.  Some guests have even described it as "magical."

host_about: I'm an east-coast transplant to the bay area. I especially love Marin and the Lake Merritt Farmer's market on Saturdays.

host_about: We are busy professionals with graduate school backgrounds.  When we are not busy with work, we love to spend time raising our family.   We are excited to open our home and meet new people who share equally in our love of the Bay Area.

name: Home in Oakland · *4.82 · 3 bedrooms · 3 beds · 2.5 baths
host_about: Steve and I are your hosts - Steve comes from a long line of Californians.  He is an alumnus of UCLA and holds a Master's in Architecture from UC Berkeley.  After living in the Haight in San Francisco and Mill Valley and Sausalito, in Marin County, he is delighted by the vivacity and excitement of Adam's Point in Oakland.  He writes a travel blog - ontheroad.guide.  I am a Chicago native, and graduate of the University of Wisconsin ( BA, MA)  (Master's in Public Health from UC-Berkeley), and I have never stopped being grateful for the perfect match  I found when I moved to Oakland thirty-six years ago, where I raised my two sons and where my grandchildren live. My neighborhood, in the vast Bay Area, forms my small community.  I know the other people who run the lake every day and the merchants, and I have watched with amusement and pride as our neighborhood has become the 'hip' place to be. After a thirty-year career as a community college English teacher, I have recently retired to enjoy my grandchildren, my partner, entertaining friends and family, indulging my reading addiction, and traveling.  We both love our home, as do the many friends and family we have entertained over the years.   It is a place of warmth and welcome, which we extend to you.

 5 things I can't live without? That depends, what first came to mind is; Joy, love of life, adventure, learning, good friends.  If back packing; a handkerchief (wash cloth, ties my hair back, wipes sweat off my brow, keeps my neck cool if wet...etc.) , soap, sarong, (beach towel, dress, blanket...) a smile, and a good small enough, but still holds all my stuff backpack.  Working world; A knock dead suit, comfortable but stylish shoes, ... O.k.  you know what I mean I think I have gone on too much here.

A life Motto:  "The more you celebrate your life the more life you have to celebrate"
"Live the life you imagine" & "treat others as you want to be treated."

bus line runs on this street, and BART is just about a mile away.

host_about:
Hi! We are Albena and Nikolay!

We are kind, friendly, considerate, respectful and easy-going. 
We share great love for design, architecture and transforming spaces. 

We are both vegetarians and world travelers. 

We are interested in social justice, sustainability, design, art and music. 
We share a great love for all people, animals, and our planet. 

We were both born and raised in Europe and currently, we've made beautiful San Francisco Bay Area home. 
Albena also has lived in Sofia, Bulgaria; Osnabrück, Germany; Berlin, Germany and Thessaloniki, Greece. 

Nikolay is a musician, landscape architect, designer and a small business owner. 

We are both friendly, respectful couple, who love to travel and explore different places and cultures!

We have designed and built this space for our family and friends visiting from Europe. 
Sometimes our family visits for 6 months out of the year, the rest of the time - we enjoy hosting the world!

Happy traveling!

name: Home in Oakland · *4.81 · 2 bedrooms · 1 bed · 1 shared bath
neighborhood_overview: It's a very central location - minutes away from Temescal, Lake Merritt, Rockridge, and Berkeley. I love living in one of the few 'destination' areas of Oakland, that also has lovely side streets for taking a stroll. I walk or run to a nearby beautiful cemetery park that is open to the public and has wonderful views of the Bay and different parts of Oakland. It's a great sunset watching spot. The Grand Lake area - including the weekend farmers market - is also within walking distance (or there's a bus) if you like to walk.
host_about: As of 11 years ago, I live in Oakland. I live in a fabulous neighborhood and have extra space so would love to share with traveling or visiting guests. I have lived in many housing arrangements, and enjoy meeting new people and respectful exchange.

name: Guest suite in Oakland · *4.92 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Rockridge is a vibrant neighborhood with lots to do and see. We are within a 10 minute walk of many shops, restaurants, grocery stores, and parks. College Avenue has everything from fine dining to family friendly spots all the way down to to dive bars. There is a great farmer's market on Sundays that is a five minute walk through a fun park for the kids. The neighboring Temescal neighborhood is within a mile and hosts some of our newer, hip additions, and best fried chicken sandwich in the business at Bakesale Betty's.

We are about 2 miles from the UC Berkeley campus.
host_about:
We've spent 20 years in the Bay Area half timing between Oakland and San Francisco.  When we made our permanent move to Oakland we looked for the best of both worlds and found it in Rockridge.  The best of the suburbs (friendly folks, huge yard, quiet!) with all the comforts of the urban life (walking distance to everything! and variety).  

When not working too much we are usually out and about in the Bay Area, crawling through the East Bay, San Francisco, Napa, Tahoe etc… 

We previously traveled the globe and are now onto the new adventure of raising child(ren), which is way more hectic than when we got stranded in a lava field in Iceland with no place to stay (pre-AirBnb days).

name: Home in Oakland · *4.90 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath
neighborhood_overview:
The neighborhood has a fun mix of students, young professionals, families, retired persons and quite a few ethnicities which gives it a very good "feel".

Though the street is very quiet, it lies parallel to two major streets in the Berkeley -Oakland area so there is a thriving vitality to the area with a lot of cafes, restaurants: (Starry Plough, Pena Cultural Center, Sweet Adeline Bakery/Cafe, The Vault Cafe, Crixa Cakes, Nomad, Jumpin' Java); Grocery Stores: Berkeley Bowl, WholeFoods), Theatre Companies: (Shotgun Players, Berkeley Black Repertory Theatre).

The Berkeley Farmers Market also happens here in the neighborhood on Tuesdays and on the weekends, the well known Ashby Flea Market (which is a lot more than a flea market) takes place at the BART station. Within a 5-minute walk there is much to do!. There is also plenty of street parking.

3-minute walk from Ashby BART! ( 20 minutes to SF!) and many major bus lines that run into both B
host_about:
My name is Erika and I 've now been a host on airbnb since 2014.

  A professional violinist I am also well-traveled and have always been interested in other cultures as well as traveling so I've really enjoyed meeting some of the wonderful guests that have come to stay with me.  My brain has also always been pretty curious so I have a very wide variety of interests from literature, philosophy, archaeology, science, the arts to the natural world (including a great love of animals).   I recently adopted a new rescue dog (a Saluki from Dubai) and have occasionally fostered other doggies :).

Though  I am a vegetarian I have no problems with those around me cooking/eating meat.  While I can have a very busy schedule at times, I still love connecting with new people and  hearing about their lives through a good conversation.    

Over the years, I've often been told I'm a good host as I love visitors and also love helping people discover all the "inside" cool places in the 
Bay Area.

name: Home in Oakland · *4.99 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 private bath
neighborhood_overview:
It is important to appreciate that, although we live on a quiet, friendly street, this is an urban setting so awareness of surroundings when walking at night is necessary. If you are driving, leave nothing attractive in your parked car - especially luggage.

Although the majority of visitors avail themselves of quick and easy access to San Francisco, our beloved Temescal is a diverse, eclectic walking neighborhood, featured in two New York Times articles. For example, within a pleasant 15-20 minute walk from your door are 78 well-reviewed eateries representing 21 ethnicities! Several are just a 5-minute walk.

Bikes and scooters are convenient to rent, and have safe, dedicated lanes to and from major transit.

Morning coffee and great breakfast, casual and fine dining are around the corner or just a pleasant stroll from home.

A leisurely 15-20 minute walk takes you to lively Piedmont Avenue, where you'll find Oakland’s historic & beloved Fe
host_about:
I ran a Bed and Breakfast Inn in Santa Fe, New Mexico and loved hosting travelers from around the U.S. and abroad.  I also enjoyed hosting and tutoring international students while studying at UC Berkeley. 
 
I am a reader, writer and, now that I am retired from teaching, a community volunteer.  In the spring and summer months I enjoy organic gardening and maintaining a tiny urban oasis to share with guests.

My family has been in California since the Gold Rush so, although I have lived in other parts of the United States and abroad,  I always come home.  An AirBnb guest myself, I understand the traveler’s need of a quiet retreat from the stresses of work and/or exploring.  I look forward to providing your "home away from home"!

name: Home in Oakland · *4.77 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
Home in Oakland · *5.0 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath
neighborhood_overview:
Oakland is an amazing city.

Our neighborhood is a gem. The view is stunning up here, it's quiet, the air is clear and the weather is fantastic everyday.

Just up the hill are some amazing parks and trails with some of the biggest trees you'll ever see. Check out Redwood Regional Park and Joaquin Miller Park.

Berkeley is 20 minutes north by car, Lake Merritt and Downtown Oakland are 15 minutes away, Oakland Airport is about 20 minutes away. San Francisco is about 30 minutes away across the Bay Bridge when traffic is light.

Just 5 minutes away at Fruitvale Avenue and MacArthur Boulevard you will find grocery stores, such as Farmer Joe's and Safeway, a gas station, pastry shop, restaurants, pharmacy, library and more!
host_about:
I'm 30 years old and originally from San Francisco, eldest of 6, Chinese-American. I moved back to the Bay Area in 2013 after living in LA for 4 years. I did my undergrad at Stanford, got my MBA at UCLA and have worked in interior design, product design, graphic and web design. 

I love to hike, throw a football, and watch the sun set. I garden on sunny days and cook when I'm inspired.

You will usually see me with a tool in my hand. I like construction and DIY projects. I built a fence recently and fix things around the house. I really like to clean. 

My wonderful girlfriend, Cathy, lives in Berkeley and my (large) family lives in San Francisco. I have a house in Oakland. I split my time between San Francisco, Berkeley and Oakland and cross the bridge almost everyday.

I love meeting people and sharing my home, and that is why I host. As a host, I want to make sure that you have everything you need to start your day right and that you have a pleasant home to return to. You'll have plenty of freedom to explore the City on your own. I'm pretty hands-off after the first day, but I'm always near my cell phone if you need help, unless I'm camping or on vacation.

As a guest, I'm quiet, independent. I like to start my day early and sleep around 11 PM. I prefer nature to cities, I like to read books, I love coffee, I travel with my girlfriend who likes the same things. 

My motto? I count my blessings.

- Nancy Quan

name: Guesthouse in Oakland · *4.96 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Experience the true Oakland lifestyle in Rockridge, a diverse neighborhood with plenty of shops and cafes, plus award-winning restaurants like A16 and Ramen and Oliveto. Walk to College Avenue and Temescal Alley, with the UC Berkeley Campus also close by.
host_about:
We're a family with two little kids and a golden retriever. We love to garden, cook, hike, go to parks, restaurants, and take our kids on fun trips.

We love the outdoors - hiking, skiing, biking - so can point you to the best places to get outside and see big trees, gorgeous coastline, and spectacular mountains just outside of our favorite place, the San Francisco Bay area. 

We've been in Oakland for 8 years after living in San Francisco for 7 years. Rockridge is a great neighborhood full of delicious restaurants and small businesses. When we're not in the city or playing in the mountains or cooking healthy food, we are traveling around the world, usually staying in Airbnbs - from Spain to Oregon and the central CA coast! We are big travelers - recent trips have been to Alaska, Brazil, Italy, Hawaii, and many local California trips. We are also cooks and foodies - so hopefully you'll get to join us for a meal or some culinary adventure in our kitchen, or we'll give you great tips on the best food spots in the Bay Area.

The real superhost of the casita is our golden retriever Mia, so hopefully you'll meet her if you stay with us!

A pleasant one-mile walk takes you to Lakeshore St.'s coffee shops, the historic Grand Lake movie theater, highly-rated Mediterranean restaurant (Shakewell's), unique local arts stores, hood's favorite bakery (Arizmendi) and popular Mexican cafe (Rico Rico), etc. A top-notch nearby public market, Market Hall, has these specialty shops for one-stop shopping: cheese, wine, de
host_about:
My husband, John, and I love our tranquil neighborhood and Oakland's vibrant social scene and weather!  After years of public service, we are both retired now but are on non-profit boards.

We enjoy entertaining our friends, neighbors and relatives.  We love all types of foods, traveling abroad, books and diverse cultural experiences.

As Airbnb hosts, we want our guests to truly enjoy their visit and privacy while being respectful of our neighbors.  We will provide information about Oakland, San Francisco, and our favorite Bay Area places, including restaurants, cultural sites and transit options.

As Airbnb guests, we are friendly, quiet and neat.  We like to immerse ourselves in the local culture and environs.  We love to travel abroad and learn about other cultures in foreign countries.  Our home is filled with mementos from travels abroad.

Enjoy the comforts of our home, large garden and walkability (to wonderful restaurants, grocery stores and shops) of our neighborhood!

Private half bath and shared full bath in house.
The backyard is sun facing, large and quiet with recent landscaping and all yours to enjoy.
We look forward to your stay~

name: Rental unit in Oakland · *4.37 · Studio · 1 bath

The neighborhood is anchored by the beautiful Lake Merritt, with a walking/biking trail around the Lake, and only a 10min walk to Lake Merritt BART, with 3 stops to SF, and access to all over the Bay.

There are several delicious restaurants and stores nearby, including dock-side dining on Lake Merritt (10min walk), a delicious local gastropub, a Vietnamese community and food, bars. The Oakland Museum of California is a great museum only a 5min walk away.

A coffee shop is just around the corner (but coffee maker included in room), grocery store & Walgreens is a 5min walk. The Laundromat is across the street.

Lake Merritt has a beautiful trail around it, small boats for rents for $10-12/hr, sailing, and a gondola boat (like Venice) where someone will poll you and your special guest around the Lake.

It is a quick walk/bike to downtown Oakland, with lots of restaurants, bars, more fun stuff to do, and a vibrant weekend scene.

The ne
host_about:
I'm a mid-30's Airbnb Host and Traveler with over a decade in the SF Bay Area, ready to help you find a great home for your short or 1+ month stay. I'm also honored to have over 250 great reviews on Airbnb. While we accept shorter reservations, we specialize in providing furnished homes for 1-12 months, and have noticed many of our customers are business travelers and travel nurses. And we know what they want!

Safe homes with amenities and transportation nearby, close to work, good office chair & desk for working at home, easy check-in without coordinating schedules, large WiFi connected TV's with Netflix to relax, personalized recommendations to meet like-minded folks, access to outdoor and fitness areas... and plenty more. As a former employee traveling for work in the finance industry, I realized that staying in hotels for long periods wasn't all it was chalked up to be... and that I could help provide a better experience for other travelers also. 

I've hosted hundreds of guests from around the US and world, and have studios to 2 bedroom apartments around the San Francisco Bay Area and Silicon Valley: 
- Mountain View
- San Jose
- Redwood City
- Oakland (quick commute to San Francisco)
- Richmond

Send me a message and let's see what we can find closest to your work that meets your needs.

I LOVE the San Francisco Bay Area, and I want you to also! I've lived here for over a decade, and there may be no other place in the world that offers the mix of opportunity, great weather, beautiful nature, urban activities, events, concerts, sporting events, and all kinds of great people.

I'll provide you my own local guide of activities, meetups for your personal interests, and do my best to enjoying your time in the Bay, being productive, staying active, and making the most of your time here (or you're welcome to relax.. we're just here when you need us.)

I have personally stayed in over 25 different Airbnb apartments around the US and the world, so I also know a thing or two about what makes a great furnished home and host. And will do my best to provide that to you. 

A little more about me personally: I've lived in California my whole life, and graduated from San Francisco State University, with a major in Economics and minor in Finance. I've lived all over the Bay Area, including most of the homes I host on Airbnb. I used to work for the State of California in bank regulation, before providing furnished homes and great stays to my guests full-time. 

I enjoy learning and sharing with other Airbnb hosts and real estate investors. In my free time, I also enjoy water color painting, karaoke, beaches, traveling, and making people happy :) 

I realize the San Francisco Bay Area gets very busy and can be quite pricey relative to other locations, so please send me a message so I can see what affordable home we can get you, before everything gets booked up. Thank you for your time.

My daughter and I have hosted many friends, foreign exchange students, and friends of friends over the years in Oakland.  I speak Spanish and some Portuguese (and English!).  My daughter has graduated from college & left the nest, so there is room in the inn at home now!  Like my great neighbors, I have owned a sweet house in Idora Park for a long time.  Home and garden projects keep me busy!

 We love the convenient walking distance to Temescal and Rockridge restaurants, farmers’ markets, monthly First Fridays - music and arts events, shops, bookstores, galleries, and transportation to San Francisco. SF is a 20 minute train ride away. A great place to stay in the Bay Area and be our guest!

Things most important to me are friends, family, nature time, swimming, and learning. Activities that occupy my time are coordinating projects in immigrant communities in the Bay Area, assisting friends and family in need, dancing, bicycling, pilotes, yoga, making muffins at Green Gulch Zen farm and weekly dinners with friends from 1 to 90.

You can walk down pedestrian paths meandering through our neighborhood to the Cal Memorial Stadium football field, Haas School of Business, Boalt Hall (Law School), or International House in about 15 minutes.

A 3 minute walk from the house brings you to an endless series of trails that weave along the hills, featuring shaded woodland with spectacular views of the Bay, including a couple that lead to great restaurant/retail districts.

Together with my wife, who is a licensed architect, I've renovated this wonderful Mid-Century home over the past several years.  She and I appreciate  architecture that is functional, clean, exciting, inspiring--and above all comfortable.   

I met my wife while working abroad on sailboats.  Together, we led many sailing trips in the Caribbean and Mediterranean Seas in our pre-professional lives.

Since becoming more land-bound, we have 2 children, now ages 15 and 12.  When the kids were smaller, we all loved exploring our 1/4 acre backyard (a pretty big usable lot for the Berkeley Hills!), or riding bikes on our quiet street (a dead-end/cul-de-sac with minimal traffic) while taking in the sweeping views of the Bay... and dreaming of when we might get back on a sailboat together again.  

Now that the kids have grown up, we finally bought a boat and are enjoying exploring the bay up close!  After an active weekend of sailing or exploring elsewhere around the Bay, we love returning to the warm comfort and serene simplicity of our house on the hill.

name: Home in Oakland · *4.90 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Oakland is often called “The Brooklyn of the Bay.” The West Oakland neighborhoods are old and transitioning and serve all walks of life — blue-collar, artists, activists, families, retired, tech, and students. You name it.

The neighborhood is gritty and beautiful at the same time. You’ll find things like street art, food trucks, greasy spoons, community gardens, an aerial arts studio, and a dog daycare, all mixed in with hints of our Black Panther roots.

The neighborhood is not for everyone. If you are looking for luxury, this may not be your place. West Oakland is an emerging, urban atmosphere. It's plenty safe but considered unpolished by some standards. There is sometimes litter and often unhoused people around BART stations, including ours. If that puts you off, you might not love it here.

What we lack in a pristinely manicured, upscale neighborhood, we make up for in character. And you can't beat the proximity to BART and, well, everywhere!

My home and my neighborhood are politically progressive and socially tolerant. We celebrate differences and practice kindness. The neighbors are friendly. We have artists, students, professionals, blue collar workers, and retirees. My house is on a busy street, but if you walk along our side streets, you will find some lovely craftsman architecture and quirky urban gardens.

Overall, this is a safe area, to the degree that any place is safe. People who are accustomed to urban living and have basic street smarts will feel comfortable here. A locked iron fence around our small property also helps with security.

A short walk, bike, or bus ride away you will discover wonderful ameniti

neighborhood_overview: Oakland is the Brooklyn to San Francisco's Manhattan! host_about:
Hi there! Lauren and Dolores live together, are partners, and run the cottage. Here is a little bit about both of them. 

About Lauren: I enjoy our 1913 Edwardian home here in Oakland. I love working with my hands, always making something or fixing something else.  So, you could see me futzing around the place with tools or a brush. I enjoy hiking in our beautiful East Bay regional parks (and beyond.) And, baby – I can cook!! You might easily find me in the kitchen rockin’ to indie folk music (or Golden Age musicals and Big Band) and making a batch of New Mexican posole! I love good beer and fine wine and spending time with Dolores laughing our butts off. I also enjoy the peace and solitude of our lovely little garden and you can find me and Dolores having coffee on the deck in the morning sun.  Professionally, I'm the Artists' Services Manager of the Merola Opera Program, contracted with San Francisco Opera.

About Dolores: I received my PhD in Film Studies at UC Berkeley and currently teach online. My area of focus is "divas" (for real!), and enjoy a good cocktail, good conversation, and all the films of Catherine Deneuve. I love old movies, good music (all kinds – even opera), and anything strange or "over-the-top." I'm looking forward to meeting you!

name: Condo in Oakland · *5.0 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview: Once a shopping district in the early 20th century, Uptown is the hottest neighborhood in Oakland. A new restaurant, indie boutique, or bar seemingly opens every other week, with nearly 125 opened in the past decade. Billed as the arts and entertainment district of Oakland, it fulfills its promise, particularly during the boisterous Art Murmur on First Fridays. But the prettiest art may be the Art Deco buildings themselves, with the crown jewels being the show stopping Fox and the Paramount theaters. The former is mostly a live music venue; the latter channels its inner flapper often (classic movies with a live organ player). Art galleries, run by the artists or by volunteers, are opening in brick warehouses. Down side streets are scenes of the start-up, DIY revolution with co-ops, an urban winery, entrepreneur hubs, and creative centers.

This home is shared with my partner, Kent, and his two kids. We have so much fun here, and really like the fact that we can offer affordable accommodations for families when we are away on our own vacations. It's a win-win!

From the Art House you can see the Bay Bridge as well as stroll 4 blocks downhill to the bustling, busy and ever interesting College Avenue, home of Cole Coffee, Market Hall, and countless more.  Two bookstores within 6 blocks, plus any-star dining up and down College.
host_about:
I'm an author, mainly history books but lately a book about the Amazon. I love outdoor adventure, desert hiking, mountain trekking,  backpacking, and wildcrafting. Village life worldwide attracts me, from Nepal to Tibet to Peru, which is why airbnb appeals. It's the same friendly outreach among people of good will that works life's magic, turning strangers into friends. .    I enjoy a cozy and colorful setting, and love to share my home with others.  My motto is "Ever Onward!" because I can't live without ideas, inspiration, new writing projects, and of course, vegetables from Berkley Bowl! Striped ones, yellow ones, round ones, skinny ones, green leafy ones....mmm.  

My own travel is often trekking, stopping at guest houses, or traveling by bus, whether in Bulgaria or China. Having written a cookbook, I'm always looking out for new recipes and unusual foods, and find that friendly chats about local cuisine often develop into longer, informative discussions.

name: Bungalow in Oakland · *4.82 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 private bath

Clubs and more restaurants are just a mile or so down Broadway into "Uptown" location of the famous Paramount Theatre! Or travel north into the Rockridge District of North Oakland. Further north and you arrive in Rockridge and the great shops, restaurants and bars there!

Like to hike: The Regional Parks in the Berkeley/Oakland Hills are spectacular destinations, or if you just want a light walk, the 3.5Mi/ 5K walk around the beautiful Lake Merritt in Oakland is easy to get to from our house and a great way to enjoy water birds who live or migrate through this area each year. You can rent boats at the Oakland Parks and Rec Sailboat House (sailing, canoes, kayaks, paddle boats) and get a different perspective on Oakland's downtown area. This lake is part of the Pacific Flyway for migrating birds and there are many different birds on th
host_about: I am a retired teacher who still works as a substitute, married to Richard who is a retired project manager for AT&T who also was an architect and builder. When we traveled (before airbnb existed) our favorite thing was wondering into a town we had never been to before and finding a random B&B for the night.  We have some great memories of experiencing the world's towns by getting up close and person with the people. Now we use airbnb for our travel plans!  We love to eat, but we can't live without coffee, and chocolate is nearly as important!

name: Rental unit in Oakland · *4.72 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
At the end of a quiet cul-de-sac, this house is just a block and a half off the main drag of Grand Ave and Lake Merritt, and within walking distance to almost everything you could want. Walkscore.com rated it a "Walker's Paradise" with a score of 91, and Very Bikable as well.

You can see the beautiful animated neon sign for the landmark Vaudeville house turned movie palace The Grand Lake Theatre from the house, and you’re a block from the best rated Farmer’s Market in the East Bay. It’s a block to the lake, and 15 minutes walk around the lake to downtown.
In addition to plenty of green park area at Lake Merritt (where you'll find half of Oakland hanging out, BBQing, and relaxing in the grass on any nice day...and with the Mediterranean climate here and close to 300 days a year of sun, most days are nice days!), within
host_about: We are a tech and sustainability consultant (me), and an acute care physician (my girlfriend) living in Oakland, CA who spend our free time "greening" (eco-friendly remodeling) our 4-unit home; staycationing with our daughter, dog, and cat; and off-the-beaten-path traveling where we can stay in unique local places with a personal touch.

name: Home in Oakland · *5.0 · 3 bedrooms · 4 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview:
The Crocker Highlands neighborhood (ours) is a pretty residential area developed in the 1920s and about 350 feet above downtown Oakland and the Bay (we have views over both and to San Francisco).
We are two houses below Piedmont which is an exclusive (and expensive) small town and only one to three miles from the best parts of Oakland as well as 5 miles to the Bay.
Hiking abounds in the Hills above our house (10 minutes to the top at approximately 1,000 feet high) or you can drive 50 minutes to Mt. Tamalpais for hikes with views of San Francisco Bay, San Francisco, the Pacific, etc. An absolutely wonderful thing to do. Leave early and you can be home by noon after a great 2 hour hike. Or head out to lunch in Marin County in places such as Sausalito or Tiburon.

name: Loft in Oakland · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Jack London Square is a historic waterfront and industrial hub that continues to grow. Container ships, ferry boats, kayaks and SUPs maneuver through the harbor lined with breweries, urban wineries, coffee, and restaurants. There is an urban winery tour (link below) you can take if you can't make it to Napa! Don't miss out on the farmers/crafts market every Sunday or taking sunset walks along the boardwalk.

Named after the legendary American novelist, Jack London worked on novels at the oldest bar in Oakland--Heinold's First and Last Chance Saloon (right on the waterfront). Built in 1883, it was a staple for incoming sailors and dock workers. Have beer here for historical sake, but if you love beer there are incredible breweries throughout the neighborhood (personal favorite is Pattern Brewery which is right across the street from the loft). They serve dumplings from the popular Good to Eat Dumplings.
host_about:
Southern California roots // Bay Area livin'. Passionate about travel, new cultures, art and meaningful connections. Looking to post up for remote work in new cities. Bonus points for good views or hot tubs. 

“Travel is about the gorgeous feeling of teetering in the unknown.” - AB

name: Rental unit in Oakland · *4.13 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
host_about:
I'm a mid-30's Airbnb Host and Traveler with over a decade in the SF Bay Area, ready to help you find a great home for your short or 1+ month stay. I'm also honored to have over 250 great reviews on Airbnb. While we accept shorter reservations, we specialize in providing furnished homes for 1-12 months, and have noticed many of our customers are business travelers and travel nurses. And we know what they want!

Safe homes with amenities and transportation nearby, close to work, good office chair & desk for working at home, easy check-in without coordinating schedules, large WiFi connected TV's with Netflix to relax, personalized recommendations to meet like-minded folks, access to outdoor and fitness areas... and plenty more. As a former employee traveling for work in the finance industry, I realized that staying in hotels for long periods wasn't all it was chalked up to be... and that I could help provide a better experience for other travelers also. 

I've hosted hundreds of guests from around the US and world, and have studios to 2 bedroom apartments around the San Francisco Bay Area and Silicon Valley: 
- Mountain View
- San Jose
- Redwood City
- Oakland (quick commute to San Francisco)
- Richmond

Send me a message and let's see what we can find closest to your work that meets your needs.

I LOVE the San Francisco Bay Area, and I want you to also! I've lived here for over a decade, and there may be no other place in the world that offers the mix of opportunity, great weather, beautiful nature, urban activities, events, concerts, sporting events, and all kinds of great people.

I'll provide you my own local guide of activities, meetups for your personal interests, and do my best to enjoying your time in the Bay, being productive, staying active, and making the most of your time here (or you're welcome to relax.. we're just here when you need us.)

I have personally stayed in over 25 different Airbnb apartments around the US and the world, so I also know a thing or two about what makes a great furnished home and host. And will do my best to provide that to you. 

A little more about me personally: I've lived in California my whole life, and graduated from San Francisco State University, with a major in Economics and minor in Finance. I've lived all over the Bay Area, including most of the homes I host on Airbnb. I used to work for the State of California in bank regulation, before providing furnished homes and great stays to my guests full-time. 

I enjoy learning and sharing with other Airbnb hosts and real estate investors. In my free time, I also enjoy water color painting, karaoke, beaches, traveling, and making people happy :) 

I realize the San Francisco Bay Area gets very busy and can be quite pricey relative to other locations, so please send me a message so I can see what affordable home we can get you, before everything gets booked up. Thank you for your time.

name: Rental unit in Oakland · *4.71 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
Rental unit in Oakland · *4.94 · Studio · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
If you are coming to Oakland for work or pleasure you probably already know that it's a happening city. West Oakland is an older part of town (our house was built in 1897) and there are lots of charming old victorian houses in the neighborhood. We have a cafe on the corner (10th & Wood) and we are in easy walking distance of some other interesting and delicious cafes (10th and Wood, Kilovolt Coffee, Horn BBQ, etc.).

Downtown Oakland has an exciting art walk and street fair on the first Friday of every month and spectacular dining options, a classic art-deco movie palace (the Paramount Theater) and a vibrant waterfront.

We live in a racially and economically diverse neighborhood that is rapidly changing. You will encounter long-term local residents, hipsters, artists, urban farmers, young families and homeless people. It's the full urban experience and might be intimidating if you're not comfortable with inner city life. Some areas within a few blocks are NOT rec

name: Rental unit in Berkeley · *4.89 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Our neighborhood is one of the most coveted in the East Bay given its high walkability score and easy access to public transportation, restaurants, coffee shops, boutiques, playgrounds, hiking, Cal campus.

Our home is a 15-20 minute walk to the Rockridge Bart station and the 3 mile strip of quaint shops and restaurants along College Ave.

Walk 15 minutes in another direction, and you’ll find the Claremont Canyon trail, a rigorous 2-mile hike straight up the Berkeley Hills that affords vast views of San Francisco, the Bay, and all three bridges. You can either walk right back down (30-45-min round trip), or meander back through Cal campus.

We are also a 10-minute walk to Peet’s Coffee, Fournee Pastry Shop and the Claremont Hotel and Spa. Cal campus is 1.5 miles away.

Your kids can burn off energy at Chabot Elementary School's large and interactive playground, right down the hill.

On the East side you have the view of the green Berkeley Hills. You are minutes from shopping, BART, U. of Berkely, Parks and the escape to Napa Valley.

Local attractions: California College of the Arts (2.8 mi.), UC Berkeley (4.6 mi.), Mills College (4.7 mi.), Redwood Regional Park (3 mi.), The Claremont Hotel and Spa (2.9 mi.), Lake Temescal (1.4 mi.), Downtown Oakland (4.5 mi.), Oakland Museum of CA (5 mi.), Jack London Square (6.3 mi.), San Francisco (13.5 mi.)
host_about:
Hello! 

We have truly enjoyed creating a space that is welcoming and comfortable for our guests. We love hosting on Airbnb and have had some wonderful experiences as Airbnb guests - most recently during trips to Tulum, Montreal, Spain & Morocco. 

Our guest suite is a private, indoor-outdoor space that is separated from the main house by a deck.  We simplified the guest spaces to make it possible to follow cleaning and sanitizing best practices during this time. The spaces are now more minimal but still feel cozy. 

We were students at UC Berkley and lived in San Francisco (and got married & had a baby) before moving to this special spot. We appreciate the wonderful diversity of people, food, art & nature found in Oakland and having been in the Bay Area for many years, we know it well.  We are more than happy to make recommendations for local restaurants, bookstores, shops, classes, hiking trails...looking for something else? We could probably make a recommendation for that too. :)

We are available if anything comes up and the separation between the main house and cottage provides our guests with space and privacy.

We offer a 10% discount for stays a month or longer.

Adams Point is a historic neighborhood in Oakland's Council District 3, which includes Uptown, Downtown Oakland, Old Oakland, Jack London Square, West Oakland, and Pill Hill. Primarily residential, the neighborhood is a mix of single family homes, condominiums, and both large and small apartment buildings. It sits on the north shore of Lake Merritt and is bounded by Grand Avenue on the south, Harrison Street on the northwest, and Interstate 580 on the northeast.

With easy access to freeways, many public transportation options nearby, and its proximity to just about every amenity and point of interest in the center of the city, Adams Point is ideally situated as a base for visitors touring the San Francisco Bay Area, visiting family or friends, or coming for business or work.

name: Guest suite in Oakland · *4.89 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
The house is located in West Oakland’s Prescott neighborhood which is know for its historic Victorians that line the streets, which were the original buildings built here in the late 1800’s. Great warm weather (especially compared to San Francisco) and a neighborhood that is quiet, with flat streets (no hills at all) makes it easy to get around (BART the subway system is a 10 minute walk away). There are areas around West Oakland with brand new condo developments, homes, as well as beautiful restored/modernized Victorian homes (like ours!) and it is growing bigger and better every day! But please note this is a city with a wide range of people from different backgrounds and socioeconomic levels, but never have had any issues for all the years we've lived here and hosted. We love the area and have the nicest people that live around me on my block. We know you will love it too!

By the way! - On the corner of my block is a phenomenal eatery that serves breakfast and lunch daily
host_about:
Born and raised just north of San Francisco, I am a native that loves the entire Bay Area. Being so close to San Francisco is so much fun, but living in Oakland is amazing and I would love to share both of my cities with you! 

I have worked in hospitality for many years and it is one of my passions, so if you need recommendations for the best the area has to offer, please just ask!

I also work from home now so I’m available if you have any needs during your stay, although your space and privacy is always a priority and you can have an entirely contactless stay if you prefer.

name: Home in Oakland · *4.91 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview:
The house is minutes by foot from the serene beauty of the Rose Garden and less than a 10 min. walk to shops and restaurants for every budget and taste on Grand Avenue. Shopping streets Lakeshore Ave & Piedmont Avenue are also nearby. There is plenty within walking distance but a car helps for hauling groceries...we also live on a hill so you may prefer a car to get around.

Take in a film at the historic Grand Lake movie theater or sing showtunes at The Alley piano bar. Get your nails did, shop curated second hand clothing at Maribel, stock up on goodies at Trader Joe's or farm fresh produce and gourmet foods at the Saturday farmer's market. Enjoy wine at Ordinaire, pastries at Bake Sum, or cocktails and California cuisine at Almond & Oak on Grand Ave. Explore Piedmont Avenue and the beautiful views in and from Mountain View Cemetery. Walk, jog, or skate around scenic Lake Merritt or take a gondola ride on it. Enjoy live music on the deck of the Lake Chalet or A
host_about:
My partner and I love to visit new cities and host guests in the fantastic Bay Area!  

Some of my favorite local spots are Lake Merritt, Cafe Romanat Ethiopian Restaurant, Burma SuperStar on Telegraph, Mountain View Cemetery for walks and views, The Grand Lake Theater, and Curbside Creamery.  

When I travel I like to feel cared for by my host and experience what it is like to actually live in another place, and I want you to have that experience at our home, too!

name: Cottage in Oakland · *4.97 · Studio · 1 bed · 1.5 baths
neighborhood_overview: Maxwell Park is a beautiful hilly neighborhood filled with California Bungalows and Mediterranean style homes, many built in the 1920s. My neighbors are diverse, friendly home owners. The homes of filled with original craftsmanship like hard wood floors, built-ins, and other old-school charm. There are lovely views of air traffic arriving and departing over the Bay, and fireworks can sometimes be seen and heard over the Coliseum following A's/Raider/Warrior games. Conveniently located close to Mill's College, the Oracle Arena, Downtown, Uptown, Lake Merritt, and the Oakland International Airport, Maxwell Park is a unique, diverse, beautifully integrated "jewel" of a neighborhood filled with Oakland pride! You'll be pleasantly surprised and feel right at home away from home.
host_about:
I'm a licensed Realtor, original music artist, video producer, and communications specialist who loves to BBQ, entertain, meet new people, and travel. I have two wonderful teens who live with me part time and family is very important to me.

I'm originally from a small town in Humboldt County CA. near the Oregon boarder, but  have lived in Oakland for nearly 20 years and am proud to call it home. I've loved watching our city grow over the years, locally known as "The Town" for our rich diversity, colorful history, and down to earth people. 

There are dozens of new restaurants, brew pubs, and shops flooding into Oakland as the cost of living and doing business in San Francisco continues to rise. The NBA Championship Golden State Warriors introduced Oakland to the world in a positive light, and the Oakland International Airport is small, super convenient, and minutes away. 

Visit our charming 1922 California Bungalow in the beautiful Maxwell Park neighborhood of Oakland, CA. Take BART (Bay Area Rapid Transit) to San Francisco ("The City") to avoid parking hassles while there. I've also put together a list of cool things to do right here in Oakland...on the "Sunny Side of the Bay!"

ABOUT MY TWO LISTINGS:

1) PRIVATE COZY COTTAGE:
We know you'll love our beautiful completely private (detached) carriage house with kitchenette, granite bar, microwave, mini-fridge, coffee maker, hardwood floors, natural light, gas heat, flatscreen TV with Roku, Netflix, and Prime Movies. There's also FREE Wifi, a music dock, open tile shower, and FREE parking in a great neighborhood. The queen sofa bed has a 2 inch memory foam topper so you'll sleep like a dream!

2) PRIVATE BUNK ROOM IN LOVELY OAKLAND HOME:
This private spacious bedroom is perfect for a single guest, or two adventurers traveling together in need two full-sized pillow-top bunk beds and locking doors. Our lovely 1922 California Bungalow offers guests a clean, comfortable, stylish place to stay in a centrally located great neighborhood with free parking. I recently added a 32 inch flat screen TV with Netflix, RoKu, and Prime movies. 

Come and go as you please through a lovely private gated backyard with redwood deck, outdoor seating, seasonal fire pit, flowers, and organic gardens. Enjoy your new cozy home away from home!

I look forward to hosting you,

--Colette

name: Home in Oakland · *4.95 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath
neighborhood_overview:
West Oakland is a neighborhood on the rise. It's got a rich cultural scene and is the home of a pretty amazing community. That said, this is an area that has seen a lot of displacement due to rising rents, and might be perceived by many as a "rougher" neighborhood.

You will encounter unhoused people (there is an homeless encampment a block away) and there is visible poverty in the neighborhood.

We recommend guests exercise caution (as in any city)— walking purposefully without staring at cellphones especially at night, being aware of surroundings, etc.

Please be comfortable with this before you agree to come and stay with us.

There are restaurants close by, but this is not a shopping district. The closest mall area is 1.6 miles away at Baystreet in Emeryville.

Berkeley Bowl and Trader Joe's -- our local grocery stores -- are about 1.1 and 1.5 miles away (respectively and in different directions).

Many of the homes were built either before the 1906 earthquake or after (like our house), so take a walk down 63rd St. and notice some of the original details (especially the block going towards San Pablo Ave).

host_about:
I'm a mid-30's Airbnb Host and Traveler with over a decade in the SF Bay Area, ready to help you find a great home for your short or 1+ month stay. I'm also honored to have over 250 great reviews on Airbnb. While we accept shorter reservations, we specialize in providing furnished homes for 1-12 months, and have noticed many of our customers are business travelers and travel nurses. And we know what they want!

Safe homes with amenities and transportation nearby, close to work, good office chair & desk for working at home, easy check-in without coordinating schedules, large WiFi connected TV's with Netflix to relax, personalized recommendations to meet like-minded folks, access to outdoor and fitness areas... and plenty more. As a former employee traveling for work in the finance industry, I realized that staying in hotels for long periods wasn't all it was chalked up to be... and that I could help provide a better experience for other travelers also. 

I've hosted hundreds of guests from around the US and world, and have studios to 2 bedroom apartments around the San Francisco Bay Area and Silicon Valley: 
- Mountain View
- San Jose
- Redwood City
- Oakland (quick commute to San Francisco)
- Richmond

Send me a message and let's see what we can find closest to your work that meets your needs.

I LOVE the San Francisco Bay Area, and I want you to also! I've lived here for over a decade, and there may be no other place in the world that offers the mix of opportunity, great weather, beautiful nature, urban activities, events, concerts, sporting events, and all kinds of great people.

I'll provide you my own local guide of activities, meetups for your personal interests, and do my best to enjoying your time in the Bay, being productive, staying active, and making the most of your time here (or you're welcome to relax.. we're just here when you need us.)

I have personally stayed in over 25 different Airbnb apartments around the US and the world, so I also know a thing or two about what makes a great furnished home and host. And will do my best to provide that to you. 

A little more about me personally: I've lived in California my whole life, and graduated from San Francisco State University, with a major in Economics and minor in Finance. I've lived all over the Bay Area, including most of the homes I host on Airbnb. I used to work for the State of California in bank regulation, before providing furnished homes and great stays to my guests full-time. 

I enjoy learning and sharing with other Airbnb hosts and real estate investors. In my free time, I also enjoy water color painting, karaoke, beaches, traveling, and making people happy :) 

I realize the San Francisco Bay Area gets very busy and can be quite pricey relative to other locations, so please send me a message so I can see what affordable home we can get you, before everything gets booked up. Thank you for your time.

neighborhood_overview:
Fruitvale is a historical and diverse, neighborhood in East Oakland. Many of Oakland's neighborhoods are undergoing rapid transition and you will see a wide variety of people from all socioeconomic backgrounds in our area. Some of our neighbors have been here for 30+ years, some for 2. (Before the pandemic) On the weekends you might find block parties and large family gatherings. We are on a thoroughfare to the rest of the neighborhood, while it's relatively quiet, please note if you are sensitive to any noise. host_about:
I'm a mid-30's Airbnb Host and Traveler with over a decade in the SF Bay Area, ready to help you find a great home for your short or 1+ month stay. I'm also honored to have over 250 great reviews on Airbnb. While we accept shorter reservations, we specialize in providing furnished homes for 1-12 months, and have noticed many of our customers are business travelers and travel nurses. And we know what they want!

Safe homes with amenities and transportation nearby, close to work, good office chair & desk for working at home, easy check-in without coordinating schedules, large WiFi connected TV's with Netflix to relax, personalized recommendations to meet like-minded folks, access to outdoor and fitness areas... and plenty more. As a former employee traveling for work in the finance industry, I realized that staying in hotels for long periods wasn't all it was chalked up to be... and that I could help provide a better experience for other travelers also. 

I've hosted hundreds of guests from around the US and world, and have studios to 2 bedroom apartments around the San Francisco Bay Area and Silicon Valley: 
- Mountain View
- San Jose
- Redwood City
- Oakland (quick commute to San Francisco)
- Richmond

Send me a message and let's see what we can find closest to your work that meets your needs.

I LOVE the San Francisco Bay Area, and I want you to also! I've lived here for over a decade, and there may be no other place in the world that offers the mix of opportunity, great weather, beautiful nature, urban activities, events, concerts, sporting events, and all kinds of great people.

I'll provide you my own local guide of activities, meetups for your personal interests, and do my best to enjoying your time in the Bay, being productive, staying active, and making the most of your time here (or you're welcome to relax.. we're just here when you need us.)

I have personally stayed in over 25 different Airbnb apartments around the US and the world, so I also know a thing or two about what makes a great furnished home and host. And will do my best to provide that to you. 

A little more about me personally: I've lived in California my whole life, and graduated from San Francisco State University, with a major in Economics and minor in Finance. I've lived all over the Bay Area, including most of the homes I host on Airbnb. I used to work for the State of California in bank regulation, before providing furnished homes and great stays to my guests full-time. 

I enjoy learning and sharing with other Airbnb hosts and real estate investors. In my free time, I also enjoy water color painting, karaoke, beaches, traveling, and making people happy :) 

I realize the San Francisco Bay Area gets very busy and can be quite pricey relative to other locations, so please send me a message so I can see what affordable home we can get you, before everything gets booked up. Thank you for your time.

name: Guest suite in Oakland · *4.90 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Montclair is a lush, wooded neighborhood in the Oakland Hills, about 17 miles from San Francisco and 10-15 minutes by car to most popular Oakland/Berkeley neighborhoods. It is nestled at the intersection of three canyons and borders several regional parks with literally hundreds of miles of hiking and bicycling trails.

Montclair Village is a 5 minute drive (or a really nice 30-minute walk along a old railroad trail), where you can find excellent restaurants and shopping.

Our guest guide is full of little-known finds and personal recommendations for places truly "Oaklandish" you can enjoy with in-person, take-out or delivery during the pandemic.
host_about:
My husband Lalo and I are both "cats with nine lives".  I am a former vocalist who now owns a nearby yoga studio (and specializes in yogic sound practices.)  Lalo is a Facilities Director with an MFA in Sculpture.  Between the two of us we have had substantial lives in dance, music, political theater, instrument making, visual arts, yoga, arts administration, marketing & public relations, and I can't even remember what else.  

I travel extensively — including taking groups of yoga students on international trips  (India, Mexico, Morocco, Italy, Cuba, Japan) — and view travel as a form of yoga, a transformative experience.   

I like to use Airbnb when I travel, and choose my rentals as much for the owners as I do for the spaces.  I love to meet interesting people, and delight in sharing with others those things I feel make life rich and beautiful.

My life motto?  Have mercy.

name: Bungalow in Oakland · 2 bedrooms · 1 bed · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview:
Our home on the map is the Rockridge neighborhood, and we're a 10-13-minute walk (depends on your pace) to BART and all the amenities of College Ave. It's flat, bike-friendly, walk-friendly, and even car friendly, as parking is easy. We're adjacent to Temescal and Bushrod, about 7 blocks to Berkeley, and about 2.5 miles to the UC Berkeley campus. The bus lines are also good and plentiful.

Rockridge's College Avenue is the retail main drag, as well as Telegraph Avenue in the Temescal neighborhood. We walk to our favorite dining destinations, Pizzaiolo and Millennium, and there are tons of options all within a 15-minute walk. Trader Joe's and Market Hall are walkable, and it's about a mile to Whole Foods. From dive bars and tacos to the Sunday farmers market to upscale cocktails and fine dining, the options are all walkable in 15 minutes or less.
host_about:
I need a comfortable, quiet place to rest with a great bed when I travel, and I like to provide that as well. I like to enjoy and provide unique, lovely spaces.

I use only earth-friendly unscented/naturally scented non-greenwashed cleaning and personal care products and need the same from my guests.

I am conscious/conscientious/thoughtful/communicative. Nonsmoker and vegetarian. I have lived in the Bay nearly 30 years and work in real estate.

name: Home in Oakland · *4.37 · Studio · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: This studio apartment is in the Allendale District. This location is in the flat lands of East Oakland. We'd only recommend booking if you have a car as this location is car-centric. The surrounding area is still urban so we recommend being city-savvy if looking to stay here (ie, don't leave valuables in car, pay attention to your surroundings). This is a working class neighborhood. There are lots of Oakland school teachers, old time Oakland residents, new Oakland transplants, and large South East Asian and Hispanic communities in this area. So as you can see, a widely diverse community. You'll see iron gates and bars still on lots of homes, fences, and windows. While this is common, all our neighbors are friendly while keeping to themselves.

name: Home in Oakland · *4.98 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 2 shared baths

10 minutes away is Lake Merritt, our city's prized "water-front" area. I am happy to point you in the right direction and provide suggestions.

Don't hesitate to contact me with more questions!

Our area is undergoing redevelopment.
Please excuse how it may look temporarily now. It will look vastly different in the upcoming year, as entirely new buildings will soon be constructed, and lots of new businesses will be opening in newly renovated buildings nearby.

Oakland is the second largest city in the San Francisco BAY AREA, and the eighth-largest city in California. With any major populated city there will be some trash, graffiti, and homeless people.

Some guests may consider that terrible or undesirable. Please understand that those are things we cannot control. This is just how life is like in a big city. Rest assured with the police station across the street, this is as safe a place in Oakland as you can find.

name: Home in Oakland · *4.94 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath

Walking the streets of  Laurel/Redwood heights is not only great exercise but also allows pleasant bay views and a look at rich and changing foliage in this family-oriented neighborhood.  You'll see people walking their dogs all through the day.
host_about:

name: Guesthouse in Oakland · *4.95 · Studio · 3 beds · 1 bath

There are great hikes very close by with great views of SF and the Bay.
host_about: I'm a busy mom. I'm married to a musician and have three young children, a young dog, chickens and goats. I love to garden, swim, practice yoga and be with my family. We love to host and look forward to meeting new people.

name: Home in Oakland · *4.73 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 shared bath
neighborhood_overview:
Millsmont is a part of Oakland known mostly to locals. It's on a hillside in the foothills adjacent to Mills College.

The area is ethnically diverse. The neighborhood is notable for its sunny weather, a rarity especially in warmer months when both the city and Berkeley get a log of fog. There are also wonderful hiking trails, meadows and redwood forests that are a five minute drive up the hill.

There's a wonderful natural foods grocery store about 5 minutes away by car - Farmer Joe's in Fruitvale.

A car is recommended, though bus service is available. BART is 3 miles away.
host_about:
I am a writer, content strategist and former documentary filmmaker. Easy going, movie loving, connoisseur of life! 

I also write about organically grown wine and can tell you everywhere to go in wine country. I'm also a former travel writer and know the Bay Area well after living here for 30+ years. 

I'm well traveled, having spent time in India (all over), Italy, Greece, England and France.

name: Home in Oakland · *4.94 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1.5 baths
neighborhood_overview: We are located in the Oakland Hills, between the restaurants of the Laurel District and the woods of Redwood Regional Park. We are close to 2 highways (13 and 580), so getting into San Francisco or to other parts of the Bay Area tends to be quick. We are 10 minutes from Rockridge, Lakeshore / Grand Avenue / Lake Merritt, and Elmwood.
host_about:
I graduated from UC Berkeley's Haas School of Business and now work in nonprofit management. I’ve worked in the environmental advocacy realm, then in sustainable food startups, and now in strategic HR.

I am into food and cooking, exercise and being outdoors.  

I love sharing tips to help you find the spot you're looking to go (craving ramen? looking for a small bookstore? looking for a good hike?). I am very clean and neat, and it's important to me that guests are as well. I've traveled a lot and have used Airbnb in several countries and think it's a lovely way both to funnel money to local people (rather than large international hotel corporations) and to see what it's like to live somewhere. I hope to provide that same experience to you as a guest!

name: Home in Oakland · *4.98 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Eastmont Hills is a diverse neighborhood of well-kept homes below the 580 freeway and several steep blocks above MacArthur boulevard. I've lived in Oakland since 1985 but only recently moved to this neighborhood, in 2017. I find new things to love about it every day! There is an open space park just a half a block away, great for stretching your legs, watching the sunset and taking in the view of Mt. Tamalpais in Marin, four bridges, and the Oakland and San Francisco Skylines. You can hear the mockingbirds singing and the owls hooting, see hawks hovering above the hillside and enjoy the brilliant magenta of bougainvillea that seems to thrive here.
To be transparent, it is East Oakland: you may hear occasional sirens from MacArthur Blvd down the hill or the momentary throb of bass from someone driving by enjoying their music a little loud; and you can't leave stuff in your car in plain view and expect it to be there in the morning. It's also not a super convenient neighborhood: pub
host_about: I grew up in the Bay Area and have lived in Oakland, CA, since 1985. I love hiking with my dogs, Olive and Leo, cooking spontaneous meals with friends and enjoying the diversity and vibrancy of Oakland. I enjoy traveling and these days often visit Massachusetts to visit two of my three young-adult kids. I can't live without trees, fresh air, my Italian stovetop espresso maker, access to organic veggies and fruits and a gas cooktop (well, I could...), and especially, my dogs.

name: Guesthouse in Oakland · *4.98 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Welcome to the sunny side of the bay. Rockridge has a microclimate that is often warm year-round, and is extremely walkable, bikeable, and shoppable. The neighborhood was largely built in the 1920s, prior to the completion of the Bay Bridge. The residential homes are mostly bungalows on well-gardened, tree-lined streets. The commercial activity is concentrated on several streets which make for nice window-shopping walks - College Ave, Telegraph Ave, and nearby Piedmont Ave.

hello world. I'm fascinated by this idea. so bit about me. I'm aging gracefully :) and a transplant from Toronto, Canada.

neighborhood_overview: I was born and raised in Rockridge and think it's the best place to live in the entire bay area.  Great food, great weather, great community, and easy access to everything.
host_about: Hi, my boys and I migrate between tahoe and oakland chasing the sun and the snow.  When we're in Tahoe we like to share our place with cool people like you.  When we're in oakland we play golf, go to baseball games, hike and bike the oakland hills, or just hang out and BBQ and drink arnold palmers in the garden. We look forward to sharing our unique property with you and hope you enjoy it as much as we do.

name: Guest suite in Oakland · *4.87 · Studio · 5 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
The guest suite is located just off the main street of International Blvd, in a residential/ commercial area near the fruitvale district. Like other developing Oakland kneighborhoods, Fruitvale can seem like a study in contrast. Celebrated for its racial diversity, it is a home to a large immigrant population (predominantly spanish-speaking) and to working-class families and these days people are paying $700K for a 1,000 square foot property here.

East Oakland's Urban Suburban mix feel, is a home to people from all walks of life. Some might say, that there is a slight touch of some interesting colorful characters. We are very close to the Coliseum Bart station and the new bus rapid transit line that is currently under construction. We live in a transit hub so our neighborhood is a bit gritty. neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is mixed residential, quiet and peaceful, with easy access to buses and freeways. The Dimond District offers an array of high-quality, authentic, award-winning restaurants, such as Soul food restaurant Southern Café that was featured on Food Networks Diners, Drive-ins, and Dives.  We have some of the most amazing BBQ, Puerto Rician food, and Mexican food all within walking distance of Tongan House. Most of the residents in our diverse neighborhood have lived in the area long term and we as neighbors all look out for each other.
host_about:

The House has a rich history housing Tongans getting settled in Oakland; we continue this tradition for diverse people of all ages to live in a respectful and supportive environment as they transition to the bay area.  Central area; public transport; Onsite manager.

neighborhood_overview:
Our spacious 2 plus bedroom 1.5 bath house is in Montclair, a lovely upscale village in the Oakland hills. It includes two bedrooms, each with a queen-size bed, bright central atrium/office with additional queen sofa bed. The house is near beautiful parks that are great for hiking and easy access to San Francisco.

Montclair Village is a charming upscale community, nestled in the beautiful, tree-covered Oakland Hills. The village has a laid-back, small town feel with over 200 retailers, service providers, restaurants, and financial services.

With it's close access to world-class hiking trails with great views of SF and the bay and bike routes, Montclair Village is a convenient spot to pick up groceries, a snack, breakfast, or even bike repair, or a massage, after a day on the trails or seeing the sites of the SF Bay Area.

name: Home in Oakland · *4.82 · 3 bedrooms · 3 beds · 2 baths

Welcome to the vibrant neighborhood of the Laurel district Nestled in the heart of the city, this area is brimming with character and offers an exciting array of experiences for every type of traveler.

Foodies will delight in the diverse culinary scene that surrounds you. From trendy cafes and eclectic eateries to hidden gems serving up mouthwatering international cuisine, there's no shortage of options to satisfy your taste buds. Don't miss the opportunity to explore the nearby farmers' markets, where you can discover fresh local produce and artisanal delights.

Art and culture enthusiasts will find themselves in a creative haven. Oakland is renowned for its thriving arts community, with numerous galleries, studios, and street art murals adorning the neighborhood. Take a stroll through the streets and immerse yourself in the vibrant colors and expressive works of local artists.

For nature lovers, nearby parks offer a serene escape. Explore the beautiful
