name: Home in Oakland · *5.0 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Temescal is one of the oldest neighborhoods in Oakland, California, located in North Oakland, and centered on Telegraph Avenue. The neighborhood derives its name from Temescal Creek, a significant watercourse in the city.

Temescal is primarily a residential neighborhood. Most of the houses in Temescal are early twentieth century bungalows along tree-lined streets. There are also many multi-family homes and mid-size apartment complexes interspersed throughout the neighborhood.

Temescal was an Italian-American neighborhood until the late 1960s. Temescal saw many changes in demographics in the past 10 years as new developments and upscale shopping and restaurants entered the neighborhood. Large numbers of young couples with children moved to Temescal as the real estate prices in nearby Rockridge grew too expensive for middle-class families. People of different racial and economic backgrounds live side-by-side in the neighborhood. Temescal is a diverse neighborhood wi

name: Hotel in Oakland · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 private bath
Guesthouse in Oakland · *4.99 · Studio · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Montclair is a charming little village just down the hill.

You'll find a variety of good-to-very-good restaurants in the village: Daughter Thai and Perle have both received excellent reviews. Crogan's is great for a burger and watching sports at the bar, as is Camber. El Agavero is a fun Mexican restaurant. We also have three Japanese restaurants.

There is a large and active farmer's market every Sunday morning.

For breakfast the Monclair Egg Shop is very popular. Also, Starbucks and Peets.

For groceries, there are two large supermarkets: Safeway and Lucky's. Both offer free parking.
host_about:
I am from England but have lived in the US for over 30 years.  Many of those years in NYC and now in the Bay Area.  I work for a nonprofit providing young girls social, emotional learning and physical activities to improve their health and self confidence.  I love to hike and garden - we have a very large garden that needs considerable attention. There are dozens of amazing hiking trails just five minutes up the road along Skyline Drive. We enjoy the theater, museums, movies, urban environments and cooking. We have recently become empty-nesters which was hard but are getting used to it!

Living in the Bay Area we are fortunate to be able to escape to beautiful places for a couple of days, such as Yosemite, Sonoma and Tahoe. We love to travel, but we are also very aware that living here is idyllic. You can't beat the weather!

As a host we like to let our guests enjoy total privacy. If they want to ask us for anything we are available, but for the most part we leave our guests alone. We have a lovely deck where they can hang out and enjoy the view (and the stars).

name: Home in Oakland · *4.51 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1.5 baths

neighborhood_overview:
What I love about my neighborhood: its cafes, proximity to all things Berkeley and Oakland, the weather, the architecture, arts district, music venues, bike lanes, trees, gardens, theaters, and a hundred other things.

I have lived here since 1987 and raised my daughter here. I love my neighborhood and want to share my experience with as many people as possible. A good walk (25 minutes) is up to College Avenue in the Elmwood district where you will find a movie theatre, terrific cafes and restaurants, Wells Fargo Bank, bakeries, ice cream shop, and so much more. Or walk more to the south on College Avenue to enter the Rockridge district for tons of shops and eating establishments.

Just a couple of blocks away on Adeline Street and Alcatraz Avenue are good eating places, a Yoga studio, and a few shops.
host_about:
I am the founder and president of a local bakery which I began in 1983 and from which I happily retired in January 2017.  My love of baking began when I was just 4 years old and spent much of my time at my mother's side while she worked in The Vienna Bakery of Tempe, AZ.  Little did I know I would move from art and dance to baking as my life's work. 

Along with baking, I love the outdoors and am most happy when I am hiking and even happier the rare times I manage to pitch a tent somewhere beautiful; like Yosemite National Park.  My musical taste is all over the map. From straight up jazz to 60's and 70's rock to music from all over the world.

I have one daughter who has given me three super charged grandchildren, whom I just adore!  You may meet them during your stay with me.

I look forward to meeting all of you who choose to visit my home.  You will find it to be very comfortable and peaceful.  Some guests have even described it as "magical."

You are minutes from the state parks, and vista points with great views of Oakland and SF, and minutes walk from commercial districts with restaurants, banks, supermarkets etc. The space is 1 block to a local organic food store (Food Mill), 3 blocks to a local supermarket (Farmer Joe's), 2 miles to the Lake Merritt district of Oakland and 30 minutes to downtown San Francisco.

Situated 1.5 miles from Joachim Miller Park, and Redwood Regional Park where you can enjoy excellent vistas of Oakland, the Bay Area and San Francisco. Enter these parks and you will quickly forget that you are minutes away from the hustle and bustle of the city. Hikers, equestrians, bicyclists, joggers and picnickers frequent these parks. The rustic woodland trails lead you through redwood groves and oak woodlands and across lush creeksides and wet meadows

Rockridge doesn't just have to serve as a base from which you can explore the Bay, it is a destination in and of itself. Any quick search will yield many things to do in the area and I'm happy to provide guidance in that regard. Immediately to the west you find the hipster haven Temescal and just to the north you find similarly comfortable Berkeley neighborhood Elmwood. UC Berkeley and hill hiking is also close by.
host_about:
Freelancer, lover of my home state California, proud UC Berkeley alum. I regard myself as a considerate and mindful person, always up for a new experience or adventure. 

I value my close friendships, having officiated 8 of my friends' weddings. I enjoy hosting and traveling, so I'm grateful to AirBnB for facilitating both.

name: Home in Oakland · 3 bedrooms · 3 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview:
OUR WONDERFUL NEIGHBORHOOD
The Glenview neighborhood, which borders on Piedmont and Montclair, is one of the most prized locations in Oakland, with two bedroom homes selling regularly for over a million dollars. It’s a quiet yet accessible area, with wonderful, open neighbors and plenty of character. 2 Blocks from our destination "Gourmet Village" (10 restaurants to choose from), stores, beauty/nail parlors, redwood trails/stream, huge park/pool/tennis/picniking, kids play area, etc. For more details about Glenview, and to see a pic of our 1.5 block business/restaurant row, find Glenview, Oakland, CA or we'll send you links!
host_about: We (Carol and Allan) are retired professionals, and love traveling as much as we love living in our beautiful home of 35 years.  We enjoy kayaking, biking, meditation, outdoor exploring, alternative cultures, and adventures. So we thought, “how perfect to share our home and amazing neighborhood/location with folks who love traveling as much as we do.”  Whether traveling for pleasure or business, or just needing a place to land for a few months, we want you to be as happy during your stay as we are in this warm and inviting house and hope that it will feel like your home away from home.  We’ve written a detailed manual covering appliances, TV/devices, etc. so your stay in our home will be smoother.  While we are away, we will have a property manager who is a life-long Oakland resident available to share information about the Bay Area at all times, and in case you need something.  We’ll also be available until Mar. 1, and later by phone in case of emergencies.  We hope you enjoy your visit to the Bay Area and hope we get a chance to meet you!

name: Loft in Oakland · *4.90 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview:
Sue (W. Oakland host) sums it up perfectly -
This is a residential neighborhood in an urban area, while quiet at night, there are the normal city and residential neighborhood sounds during the day. This neighborhood is in a transitional state and described by some as "gritty." I have lived here 12 years and love the weather, close approximation to SF and the wonderful diversity of my neighbors! name: Guest suite in Oakland · *4.87 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Clawson, known colloquially as Dogtown, is a dynamic and rapidly changing urban area in West Oakland bordering Emeryville. It is centrally located in the San Francisco Bay Area, with easy access to many interesting places, a vibrant restaurant and arts scene, and rich ethnic, racial, and economic diversity. It is important to note that Oakland, probably more than any other West Coast major city, has suffered in a disproportionate way from a housing crisis, with a significant and visible homeless population. These people are living in this neighborhood, a mere stone’s throw from homes that frequently cost one million dollars or more.

Solutions to these complex issues are not completely clear, but please be aware that you will be staying in an urban environment, with all of the advantages and potential inconveniences that may imply.

name: Home in Oakland · *4.52 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 4 shared baths
neighborhood_overview:
HISTORY
Peralta Hacienda Historical Park is THE place to learn about the history of Native and Mexican Americans in Oakland. It's full of tours, events, youth programs and interactive museum exhibits. The six-acre park is made up of three areas the historic core adobe area, 1870 Peralta House and the Peralta Creek nature area.

FOOD
One of the most beautiful things about Fruitvale, the taco trucks! Fruitvale is home to quite a few so we suggest sampling all over. A few of our favorites are Taqueria Sinaola, Guadalajara, and Pipirin.

ART
Hit the streets as Fruitvale boasts some of the best street art/murals in Oakland. The Rue de Merde, (which technically is in the adjacent neighborhood, Jingletown) is a mural wall composed of nearly a dozen murals and mosaics.

NEAREST GROCERY
Supermercado Mi Tierra, only 3 blocks away.

NEAREST LAUNDROMAT
Washtime Coin Laundry, also only 3 blocks away.
host_about: I am an Oakland Native that loves my city very much.  Being able to see the diversity that this city offers is a blessing.  I'm excited to be able to host such a cool property that everyone around the world can stay at.  I look forward to helping you with any questions you have about  Oakland and the neighboring cities.

name: Home in Oakland · *5.0 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath
neighborhood_overview:
Much of Oakland's charm in my opinion is in its ethnic, race, class and political diversity, and the vibrant San Antonio district is a classic representation of this cross-section. My neighbors come from many parts of the world but we share food, fruit, and greetings while we walk our dogs and kids up the block. The street is tucked up on a hill away from the major thoroughfares, with sun and breeze and views of the Bay sparkling to the west and the city skyline to the north - but it's under 2 miles from downtown Oakland with its off -the-hook restaurant and club scene, street life, and BART connection to the broader Bay.
Coming home from the bustling, challenging city I love feels like returning to an oasis of calm and peace. You're welcomed to join us there!
host_about: I am a health care provider and an avid outdoorswoman.  Since moving to the Bay Area I have enjoyed rowing crew on Lake Merritt, cycling the network of bike-friendly roads in the Bay Area, hiking and running with my 2 viszla dogs, and backpacking in the Sierra and elsewhere.  I also very much enjoy sustainable organic gardening and trail maintenance.  I totally groove on cultural exchange.  For me, running this inn is a natural outgrowth of being a returned Peace Corps Volunteer (Ivory Coast, '97-99), speaking Spanish, French and German, and always looking for the most realistic and genuine reflection of a community when I travel abroad. I hope to reflect the best of Oakland to my guests, while learning some about the world from my guests and their experiences.

name: Rental unit in Oakland · *4.79 · Studio · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Located in historic Old Oakland district. Many buildings in the area were built in the 1800's.

Our area is undergoing redevelopment.
Please excuse how it may look temporarily now. It will look vastly different in the upcoming year, as entirely new buildings will soon be constructed, and lots of new businesses will be opening in newly renovated buildings nearby.

Oakland is the second largest city in the San Francisco BAY AREA, and the eighth-largest city in California. With any major populated city there will be some trash, graffiti, and homeless people.

Some guests may consider that terrible or undesirable. Please understand that those are things we cannot control. This is just how life is like in a big city. Rest assured with the police station across the street, this is as safe a place in Oakland as you can find.

Please rate us fairly on accuracy of pictures, description of space and cleanliness of room and building, and not unfairl
host_about:
All responsible and respectful guests are welcome to book! 

We aim to provide the best hospitality that we can and hope each guest has a pleasant stay.

Oakland is the second largest city in the San Francisco BAY AREA, and the eighth-largest city in California. With any major populated city there will be some trash, graffiti, and homeless people.

Some guests may consider that terrible or undesirable. Please understand that those are things we cannot control. This is just how life is like in a big city. Rest assured with the police station across the street, this is as safe a place in Oakland as you can find.

Please rate us fairly on accuracy of pictures, description of space and cleanliness of room and building, and not unfairl
host_about:
All responsible and respectful guests are welcome to book! 

We aim to provide the best hospitality that we can and hope each guest has a pleasant stay.

Any questions? Please feel free to ask and be sure to read the entire descriptions of listing, neighborhood descriptions, and house rules before booking!

name: Home in Oakland · *4.20 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 2 shared baths

name: Guest suite in Oakland · *4.98 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Visitors can soak up the Bay Area from our space. Walking distance to the shops and restaurants in Temescal, as well as a hop, skip & jump to Berkeley and Emeryville for more shops and dining. Enjoy Lake Merritt, downtown Oakland at First Friday’s street fair, as well as food trucks & DJ at the Oakland Museum every Friday night.

San Francisco is just ACROSS THE BAY BRIDGE by BART or car - takes about 20-30 min drive (depending on traffic). Freeway access is four blocks and three BART stations within 1 mile each (a 20-25 minute walk or a 5 minute Uber/Lyft ride.)

Farmers Markets on Tuesdays and Saturdays are walking distance, as well as a natural organic produce store and a Whole Foods. Peet’s Coffee and Noah’s Bagels is around the corner, as well as corner markets and gas stations.

Rendezvous is a popular restaurant right around the corner on MLK Blvd, to the right.
host_about:
Education Leader
California native, Bay Area resident. 
Wife, Camille, and two kids enjoy family building activities, road trips, spoken word, dancing, and homemade guacamole.  

Excited to see travelers find the bold & brilliant beauty of our town - OakTown - and the amazing wonders of the San Francisco Bay.

name: Guest suite in Oakland · *4.96 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: We love Oakland and it’s gorgeous weather.  However,  Oakland is one of these cities that has extreme diversified neighborhoods.  We are proud to say our home is located at a safe, quiet, and woodsy neighborhood with private security patrols.  Blocks from the breath taking Bay, city & bridge view from Oakland Temple. Few mins drive to Montclair Village shopping and great restaurants!  5 min drive or 20 mins scenic walk to Joaquin Miller Park and Chabot Space Center.
host_about: We have been living in this beautiful San Francisco Bay Area for over 30+ years.  We love traveling and meeting great people.  Meanwhile we enjoy hosting responsible and respectful guests from all around the world!

name: Home in Oakland · *4.50 · 4 bedrooms · 6 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview: We are a short walk and even shorter drive to Montclair village where you can find shops, restaurants, cafes, and grocery stores. We are also a short walk from some of the most beautiful hikes in Oakland.
host_about: Choreographer based in Brooklyn. Hubby is a contractor. We're both musicians as well. We have a cute little dog named Lucy. And in 5 months we'll add two identical infants to the family! Woohoo!

name: Guesthouse in Oakland · *4.82 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Located a few blocks from the Berkeley border, three blocks from Children's Hospital and six blocks from Oakland's buzzing, hip Temescal District. There's a great cafe a block away for your morning cappuccino. After that, just walk or drive six blocks to Temescal district where you have your choice of Burmese, Korean, Thai fusion, Japanese, Caribbean, Italian, Fried chicken and more ... and more food and shopping. Hang outdoors at Temescal Brewery.

Walking or driving north from my place, you will find Sweet Adeline, one of Berkeley's sweetest cafes, fresh baked goods, yum, etc. Also, there is an amazing Farmer's Market Tuesday afternoon/evenings. Half a mile after that is Ashby BART and a little further is Berkeley Bowl, Berkeley's famous grocery store for everything you need. Whole Foods is about the same distance, up Ashby St from BART.
host_about:
I have been in the Bay Area for 20+ years.  I have worked predominantly in social justice and the environment. I really like for people to be happy. So, whether it's at work, or in my airbnb, I try hard to please. Good communication is important to me. I love traveling and talking to strangers. 

I am a big camper/backpacker and have a Buddhist practice.

I have enjoyed both staying with Airbnb hosts and being a host. Most recently, I have stayed in Airbnbs from Tehachapi, CA, USA to Jerusalem, Israel. 

I founded a company called Prosper Street Technologies to market the Wave, a computer keyboard I invented.

name: Home in Oakland · *4.29 · 1 bedroom · 3 beds · 3 baths
neighborhood_overview:
HISTORY
Peralta Hacienda Historical Park is THE place to learn about the history of Native and Mexican Americans in Oakland. It's full of tours, events, youth programs and interactive museum exhibits. The six-acre park is made up of three areas the historic core adobe area, 1870 Peralta House and the Peralta Creek nature area.

FOOD
One of the most beautiful things about Fruitvale, the taco trucks! Fruitvale is home to quite a few so we suggest sampling all over. A few of our favorites are Taqueria Sinaola, Guadalajara, and Pipirin.

ART
Hit the streets as Fruitvale boasts some of the best street art/murals in Oakland. The Rue de Merde, (which technically is in the adjacent neighborhood, Jingletown) is a mural wall composed of nearly a dozen murals and mosaics.

NEAREST GROCERY
Supermercado Mi Tierra, only 3 blocks away.

NEAREST LAUNDROMAT
Washtime Coin Laundry, also only 3 blocks away.
host_about: I am an Oakland Native that loves my city very much.  Being able to see the diversity that this city offers is a blessing.  I'm excited to be able to host such a cool property that everyone around the world can stay at.  I look forward to helping you with any questions you have about  Oakland and the neighboring cities.

name: Home in Oakland · *4.82 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath
neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood is a working class neighborhood, vibrant and full of wonderful long time neighbors and newbies. We are a diamond in the rough (so yes its a bit sketch) but there have been newer things happening. In-n-Out Burger is nearby as well as new breweries.
host_about:
I'm a relatively shy guy but over time I'm come out of my shell, like a turtle. I love doing different things each day whether it's trying out different foods, doing impromptu random stuff like going to dance shindig (not huge party).

I am more personable in smaller groups over bigger settings. Hanging out with friends, drinking local and craft beers, and having cool chat is perfect for me. I love exploring the city and its neat spots, and seeing the sight and sounds, and meeting people.

I am also a type of person who plays classical music very loud in a car if another car next to me plays loud contemporary pop-rap music.

I am mainly busy but I really want to have time to enjoy life. Hopefully along the way I'll get to meet you, interesting people, places, and houses.

host_about:
Aloha, e komo mai! 

We shared a dream of retiring in Hawaii, and how awesome it would be to take our daughters on vacation there every summer. So, we found a home that needed some TLC. In a macadamia nutshell, our dream became a reality when we purchased our Hawaii home in 2015. This could not be possible if it wasn’t for God’s goodness all the time in our life. Therefore, to share in our lifelong dream, we invite you to come and enjoy your stay in our “Laule’a Ohana Hale” (peaceful family home) on the Big Island of Hawaii. Also, if you happen to need a place to stay in the East Bay (Northern Cali), we got a cozy studio, “Piedmont Pines Cottage” for you.

Mahalo nui loa!
Dewane & Charlyne Bradford
“Follow your Dreams!"

name: Cottage in Oakland · *4.97 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: The Golden Gate neighborhood is a quiet residential neighborhood with easy access to errands (5 min drive) or a nice walk (20 mins). Most guests who stay here are visiting family within walking distance. Lots of green parks and walking paths. The beautiful Emeryville Greenway runs through it, it's a pedestrian path that follows old train tracks through what used to be a warehouse district, now biotech corridor. There are a few casual restaurants within 5-20 minute walking distance that we highly recommend: Paradise Park Cafe, Spoon (Korean), and Cafe Colucci (Ethiopian). Townhouse (brasserie) has a nice atmosphere and is a little more expensive. The Emeryville Public Market has many ethnic cuisine choices and a lively atmosphere. For Oakland's famous food scene, travel a short distance by car to other neighborhoods. Bay Street Mall and AMC Theater are a 15 minute walk/3 minute drive. 20 minute stroll down the Emeryville Greenway pedestrian path to famed Berkeley Bowl West for the groce
host_about: I am the principal of an art gallery, and my husband Sam is a working artist and facilities manager. TIP! If you like the look of this listing and your dates are flexible, try searching WITHOUT selecting any dates and you'll see our booking calendar for the next 12 months and the full picture of availability.  We look forward to hosting you! -Marianna

name: Rental unit in Berkeley · *4.95 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
host_about: Born in England, now living in California for many years.  Two (!!) graduate degrees from UC Berkeley.     I have been an Airbnb guest in the US and several other countries and have appreciated the experience of staying in a real home, a place with warmth and character, in an interesting walkable neighborhood.   That’s what my co-host (my husband Jack) and I offer you, too, in Berkeley – a vibrant town with an internationally renowned university, distinctive architecture, innovative restaurants, serious coffee houses, bookstores, parks, museums, theater, a lively music scene – and conveniently close to San Francisco.

name: Rental unit in Oakland · *4.79 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: A very walkable neighborhood in what people have coined "hipster" so you get some urban and lots of trendy. Just a block away from a popular local pub kingfish, 2 blocks from a Whole Foods, 2 blocks from a weekly farmers market, 2 blocks from bakesale betty's, and within a mile and about 15-20 minutes to either Macarthur or Rockridge Bart.

name: Home in Oakland · *4.85 · Studio · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: The Laurel District is one of the many culturally diverse neighborhoods in Oakland. We're situated between the foot of the Oakland hills and Mills College between the High Street & 35th Avenue exit off the 580 East 26 minutes from San Francisco. From the 580 West, take the 2rd MacArthur Exit It's also easily accessed from the Redwood Highway from Berkley or Diablo Valley. The Laurel District lies at an elevation of 226 feet (69 meters). At the heart of the neighborhood lies MacArthur Boulevard, a bustling shopping area with annual festivals and many local shops, restaurants and cafes. We're one long lot away from the main street of Laurel District, MacArthur Blvd, with the northwest end at 35th Avenue (Farmer Joe's Market and Grocery, and the southeast end at High Street (Walgreens Pharmacy). There's a Goodwill just down the street if you enjoy thrifting!
host_about: I'm from Alaska. I like making pie, discussing ideas that can make life more enjoyable for everyone, and cuddling with other people's cats. Uniquely shaped fruit makes me happy, like this heart-shaped lemon from my house-sitting client's tree.

name: Home in Oakland · *5.0 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath
neighborhood_overview:
Much of Oakland's charm in my opinion is in its ethnic, race, class and political diversity, and the vibrant San Antonio district is a classic representation of this cross-section. My neighbors come from many parts of the world but we share food, fruit, and greetings while we walk our dogs and kids up the block. The street is tucked up on a hill away from the major thoroughfares, with sun and breeze and views of the Bay sparkling to the west and the city skyline to the north - but it's under 2 miles from downtown Oakland with its off -the-hook restaurant and club scene, street life, and BART connection to the broader Bay.
Coming home from the bustling, challenging city I love feels like returning to an oasis of calm and peace. You're welcomed to join us there!
host_about: I am a health care provider and an avid outdoorswoman.  Since moving to the Bay Area I have enjoyed rowing crew on Lake Merritt, cycling the network of bike-friendly roads in the Bay Area, hiking and running with my 2 viszla dogs, and backpacking in the Sierra and elsewhere.  I also very much enjoy sustainable organic gardening and trail maintenance.  I totally groove on cultural exchange.  For me, running this inn is a natural outgrowth of being a returned Peace Corps Volunteer (Ivory Coast, '97-99), speaking Spanish, French and German, and always looking for the most realistic and genuine reflection of a community when I travel abroad. I hope to reflect the best of Oakland to my guests, while learning some about the world from my guests and their experiences.

Close to public transportation and BART( Bay Area rapid transportation ) shopping: Target, Office Depot, IKEA , Best Buy, Pack N Save and Bay Street for Additional shopping.
Great location!

Hi I’m Pearl, energetic, creative , avid reader and a retired educator. 
My passion is interior decorating and gardening. My succulent garden speaks for itself with love and the care that I give to each plant often . There are many plants around my home and in the  back yard . 
I spend a lot of time volunteering and feeding the homeless. 
A Pearl that’s who I am a precious stone with many gifted attributes. Thank you

name: Home in Oakland · *4.73 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 shared bath
neighborhood_overview: Up and Coming (gentrifying) Neighborhood is generally safe. Apartment neighbors may have occasional parties, but end by 10pm on the weekends. Neighbors do have a barking dog. During the week, is generally quiet. Plenty of children that play outdoors. Community garden and elementary school 4 blocks away.
host_about:
Born & raised in the North Shore on beautiful island of Oahu. Moved to California in 1998.  Married and currently the Daddy of 3 Monkees and my family is my passion.

Being from Hawaii, naturally am laid back and chill. Enjoy listening to wide variety of music and love movement & dance. Food is always a plus!

name: Guest suite in Oakland · *4.96 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: This is new, carefully appointed studio unit is in the Oakland Hills, with a lovely open space within walking distance. It's a 10-minute drive to Oakland Zoo, Lake Chabot, Mills College, and the Oakland Coliseum. The nearest BART station is also at the Coliseum and from there you can be in San Francisco in just 15 minutes. We are avid travelers and frequent users of Airbnb ourselves, and have strived to identify the very best of places we've stayed.
host_about: Chris and I have lived in the Bay Area for over 20 years and we love everything this place has to offer. I'm an outdoor enthusiast and can advise guests on tons of activities from here to the Nevada and Oregon border. Chris is an avid sailor with plenty of local sailing adventures under his belt. Feel free to ask us about fun things to do in these parts! We've traveled abroad, extensively, usually for adventures such as scuba diving, hiking, biking, water adventures. We can communicate in Spanish (some French, but don't count on it!).

name: Rental unit in Oakland · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Lake Merrit: https://www.lakemerritt.org/
" Lake Merritt in Oakland, California is one of the most unique urban spaces in the United States. Its three mile heart-shaped shoreline in the center of an exceptionally diverse city is the place for man and nature to migrate and mingle daily. This tidal lagoon is also home to the oldest designated wildlife refuge (1870) in the United States."
host_about:
Erika Gentry is a Visual Artist and Educator. She specializes in digital imaging, photography, education, multi media arts and fine art printing in the Bay Area. An early advocate of the creative digital domain, she has been teaching and presenting electronic arts and photography at the institutional, organizational and individual levels nationwide since 1996 and has been a consultant to many of the industry’s leading professional photographers as they converted from film to a digital work-flow. She has worked in freelance photography, magazine and book picture editing, art direction, advanced digital post-production, web design and as a curator and educator. She has taught one-on-one and group courses at corporations and colleges such as The Rochester Institute of Technology, The San Francisco Art Institute, Foothill College, City College of San Francisco and Rayko Photo Center. She is currently an Associate Professor at City College of San Francisco.

Gentry grew up in Portland Oregon and received her bachelor of arts degree from The School of Journalism and Communications at the University of Oregon in Eugene. She completed her master of fine arts degree at The School of Imaging Arts and Sciences  from New York’s Rochester Institute of Technology. Her personal photographic projects explore issues of identity as expressed through the use of technology. She exhibits her art work nationally and served on the National Board of Directors for The Society for Photographic Education, the advisory board of Lensculture Magazine and is former Vice President to the Board of Directors for Fotovison. She is currently on the Board at SF Camerawork.

name: Home in Oakland · *5.0 · 4 bedrooms · 3 beds · 2.5 baths
neighborhood_overview: Crocker Highlands, an affluent neighborhood of Oakland, California, overflows with an abundance of character and charm, described as having "the genteel ambiance of an old Hollywood movie set," It is a small, walkable neighborhood with shaded, tree-lined, curvilinear streets lined with gracious traditional homes of varying architecture (many built in the 1920s and 1930s) that follow the natural contours of the topography, providing easy access to coffee shops, fine restaurants, retail, Lake Merritt, and public transportation.
host_about: My name is Kate and I live in Oakland with my husband Brian and our 2 kiddoes. We work in tech, like to travel, and occasionally we rent our place out when we do.

neighborhood_overview: In the Cleveland Heights neighborhood in Lake Merritt. We are close to the 580 for very easy driving access, and there are very accessible bus options for anyone looking to take transit. The main bus line into San Francisco runs from a stop just short 7 minute walk from the apartment, taking you into the city in 30 minutes. name: Guest suite in Oakland · *4.83 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: The house is located in a quiet small hill-side neighborhood. There are tons of restaurant and bars on the Grand Ave/Lakeshore Area and in the downtown Oakland area. Lake Merritt is a mere two blocks away where you can BBQ, lay in the grass, or jog around the perimeter.

The apartment and street are super quiet and relaxing, but less than a mile to dozens of businesses and BART station. There's a giant farmer's market right down the street, outside the much-loved art deco movie theatre.

East Bay boasts an endless number of beautiful parks, lakes, and hikes. If you have a chance, June + July in California is the time for swimming holes and camping all within an hour or two.

Otherwise, I split my time between cooking, playing records, and exploring all the beautiful woods and coastline of California.

name: Rental unit in Oakland · *4.93 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath

The fun and popular Rockridge and Temescal neighborhoods are some of the best in Oakland. The apartment is centrally located just a couple blocks in either direction to these highly walkable neighborhoods found on College, Claremont and Telegraph Avenues. You will be delighted to find an abundance of coffee houses, markets, cafes, pubs, boutiques, parks, playgrounds and more.

We are 2.5 miles to the UC Berkeley campus and a few blocks from CCA. Trader Joe's and Whole Foods are very close by. We are also very close to other great neighborhoods such as Piedmont, Lake Merritt and Montclair The lovely hills and redwood forest are just a fifteen minute drive away.
host_about: I'm a guitarist, I've worked in the music industry for many years. I love traveling, and I love hosting with Air BnB - helping to introduce new people to our sweet neighborhood and the Bay Area.

name: Rental unit in Oakland · *4.60 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
We are a short walk from BART, so guests can visit much of San Francisco, Oakland and Berkeley without a car. Some guest just come straight from the airport and only rent a car for a trip to the redwoods, shoreline or wine country.

There are many restaurants, a couple supermarkets, a movie theatre and a few clubs all in short walking distance. This neighborhood is very up and coming; there are always new places opening up.

Some guests have been on business trips and it was a great place to access San Francisco or downtown Oakland on public transit.

name: Loft in Oakland · *4.67 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Once called The Harlem of The West, West Oakland was a thriving African American community where many of the great Jazz & Blues legends visited when touring the Bay. Historically significant in many ways, the neighborhood is still diverse in culture, class and rootedness. The architecture is defined by centuries old Victorians, commercial and residential industrial spaces and contemporary mixed use structures, as well as the the Middle Harbor Shoreline Park with a stunning view of the SF Bay and San Francisco skyline and the Port of Oakland, itself.

Markets, cafes, shopping, restaurants and bars are all within a mile or 2.
host_about: I love to travel and connect with people.  I've enjoyed sharing my home in an open and honest way, with like-minded people.  The Bay Area is a wonderful place to live and I look forward to sharing with you.

name: Home in Oakland · *4.78 · 3 bedrooms · 4 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: The house is in the shadows of the  The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints and shares a similar view. It is also only a short distance to Lake Merrit and the Oakland down town and waterfront and a 20 to 30 minute car ride to San Francisco, traffic dependent.

name: Home in Oakland · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath
host_about: I'm just a kind and understanding person that believes in doing what's right when and where I can.

name: Guest suite in Oakland · *4.94 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
The home is located in Rockridge, which is one of Oakland’s oldest and most vibrant shopping/dining areas as well as most sought-after residential communities. Rockridge is ultra-walkable and filled with independent shops, bars, restaurants, cafes, grocery stores, and it's own BART station. Most of these are located on the main thoroughfare of College Avenue - which features classic old architecture on a pedestrian-scale merely 3 blocks from your door.

There is an elementary school at the end of our block, so be prepared to hear the giggles and voices of happy children if you are sitting on the porch/patio during the school hours. Drop off and pickup times create a parade of parents and caretakers walking/biking/driving through.

Super convenient location where you can walk to:

- Bikesharing (Ford Go Bike) station within 2 blocks!

- Cafes, bars/pubs and purveyors of craft cocktails, workout spaces (yoga, pilates, gyms), and independent shops<
host_about:
I am a lover of design, travel and making a difference as an individual, as a means to create change in our ever evolving world.

I am an artist, property manager and designer, entrepreneur, lover of good food and good people.  I come from the hills of Pennsylvania followed by 20 years in New York City, before coming  west to find a more balanced, creative and authentic lifestyle in the San Francisco Bay area.

I enjoy refurbishing my 100-plus-year old triplex in Oakland with my partner and dogs, immersing myself in other cultures and countries, good food, small company performances, film festivals, architecture, art, fashion, sunny days, and social responsibility.
 
Let me know what else I can tell you.

name: Home in Oakland · 4 bedrooms · 1 bed · 1.5 baths
neighborhood_overview: This is an older neighborhood undergoing an influx of the younger generation. House is on a narrow street that deadends. Uphill multilevel house with friendly neighbors.
host_about: My daughter showed me this website and I love to use it to book family vacations (often at the last minute).

name: Home in Oakland · 3 bedrooms · 3 beds · 2.5 baths
neighborhood_overview: This is a very quiet, friendly neighborhood which borders on a large field where neighbors enjoy walking.  There is a true country feeling to this sanctuary in the midst of the city.  Our home feels very private but looks out over the S.F. Bay with lovely views through unique leaded glass picture windows.  Palm trees provide ample garden shade and  a regular late afternoon breeze usually cools us off even on hot summer days. Two weekly farmers' markets are nearby.  Public and semi-private swimming pools are also nearby (Mills College and Dimond Park Lion's pools).  Less than a mile away, Park Blvd. hosts one of Oakland's "gourmet ghettos,"  with wonderful restaurants and a coffee shop to which you can walk!
host_about: I'm a retired Montessori school teacher/administrator and a pianist.  My recently deceased husband was a retired professor of classics and philosophy. He also played the clarinet and wrote.  Our home is filled with books and music.  ! love to garden and to cook.   I play the piano, read, write, swim, and enjoy riding my recumbent tricycle.  I plan to do some traveling.

host_about:
Hi! We are Albena and Nikolay!

We are kind, friendly, considerate, respectful and easy-going. 
We share great love for design, architecture and transforming spaces. 

We are both vegetarians and world travelers. 

We are interested in social justice, sustainability, design, art and music. 
We share a great love for all people, animals, and our planet. 

We were both born and raised in Europe and currently, we've made beautiful San Francisco Bay Area home. 
Albena also has lived in Sofia, Bulgaria; Osnabrück, Germany; Berlin, Germany and Thessaloniki, Greece. 

Nikolay is a musician, landscape architect, designer and a small business owner. 

We are both friendly, respectful couple, who love to travel and explore different places and cultures!

We have designed and built this space for our family and friends visiting from Europe. 
Sometimes our family visits for 6 months out of the year, the rest of the time - we enjoy hosting the world!

Happy traveling!

We love Oakland and hope that you will too! Often referred to as the “Brooklyn of the Bay”, Oakland offers a little bit of old and a little bit of new: culture, diversity, good food, amazing people, and sunshine.

The West Oakland neighborhood is a vibrant, residential neighborhood that is transitioning and becoming home to many types of people — working class families, artists, social justice activists, students, and grassroots organizations. The neighborhood is rich in history and pride. You’ll find plenty of street art, community gardens, small businesses, shipping containers, warehouses, and beautiful Victorian houses.

The neighborhood is urban, gritty, and beautiful. It is safe and centrally located, so the surrounding blocks are busy. Within walking distance you will find: a grocery co-op, coffee shop, giant dog park and playground, post office, taco truck, corner stores, and our favorite bar called 7th West.

Longfellow is a rapidly gentrifying neighborhood of Oakland full of character buildings and a few diverse characters. Please exercise caution and good judgement as you would in other urban areas dealing with homelessness and urban poverty. As a single woman, I've never felt unsafe here (being on a well-lit main street helps!) but do not expect a quiet suburb either.

For those wanting to check out a few local gems, don't miss Eli's Mile High Club for live jazz and local artists, Wally's for the best middle-eastern (eat at the counter and chat up your neighbor), Subrosa Coffee on MLK, and Hometown Heroes, Kebabery, and Arthur Mac's Tap and Shack!

Booking Requests:
Please include a bit about yourself and whoever is coming with you along with the purpose of your trip, especially if you don't have reviews already.
host_about:
Always up for an adventure, a good book, a great glass of wine, and delectable local cuisine, I'd like to be a global nomad and travel to every part of the world, if I could. At the moment, I run startups in recycling, renewable energy, and curated travel. In fact, it was by listing my home in Somerville (just outside Boston) that I was able to fund my first company. So thank you to all the travelers who've made this dream possible! 

As a host: I'm glad to open up my home in Somerville that I painstakingly renovated and now co-host with my mom (who is in California but much closer than I am!). It's a delightful spot that lets you explore locally (Union Square!) and also make the most of Cambridge and Boston too! A great base for a single person, couples, and families alike. 

As a guest: I will treat your home as if it were my own and would love to get tips on your favourite spots to eat and activities, places, music, and events to explore. If you have books about local history, culture, or even novels you can recommend, I'd love to hear about them and even discuss them over a meal or coffee/tea with you!

I highly recommend you take a nice little drive around the lake or park close by and have a nice walk around the lake, jump on a lime scooter, or have a jog around! Lots of coffee shops, restaurants, and activities to partake in the area. The weekends will have gatherings for drum circles, bbq, and lots of leisurely activity.

You can also take a 5 minute walk up the street into the Dimond area where grand lake kitchen is located and enjoy some breakfast with a mimosa! Enjoy some Cafe Umami up there street as well and enjoy the BeeHive as well. Lots of convenient shops and restaurants are located walking distance from the home!
host_about:
There’s something about constantly moving around that I find exciting and rewarding. 

I’ve met some wonderful people and learned a wealth of information about different cultures, their foods, music, entertainment, and beautiful scenery!  

I hope I can provide the same experiences with my stays and also when I visit! :)

name: Rental unit in Oakland · *4.84 · Studio · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: We are very close to UC Berkeley, Oakland Tech and Berkeley High, as well as 5 different grocery stores, 2 Walgreens drug stores and 2 walkable neighborhood kids’ parks. It’s a great place to stay during graduations, family visits, and the myriad  conferences, parties and cultural events that San Francisco and the East Bay offer.

name: Home in Oakland · *4.38 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 2 shared baths
neighborhood_overview:
This neighborhood is one of the oldest neighborhoods in West Oakland. The people here tend to be nice and friendly.

There are a variety of coffee shops, KilaVolt & Milky Way that are around a 5–10-minute walk from here and 10th & Wood is just a few blocks further.

Mandela Food Co-op (organic, local grocer & deli) is 1 1/2 blocks away and Donuts and Burgers, (good burgers) is right across 7th Street from the Bart Station.

Other retail stores such as Target, Nordstrom's rack, Ulta, and Pak N Save are about 10 minutes via Uber/Lyft.

name: Cottage in Oakland · *5.0 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
This area is a residential area that is very quiet. However, the distances to restaurants and activities are extremely convenient. Close to the house you have Park Blvd., which has lots of eateries and is close to Rocky's Market. Montclair Village is a 5 min drive, which has all of the essentials, including grocery stores, Rite Aid, CVS, restaurants, and other local shops and business. Redwood Park is a 10 min drive filled with tons of trails for hiking and biking.

Freeway access is very quick and easy via highway Highway 13 and I-580. San Francisco is about 20 minutes away, or a convenient commute via BART from nearby Rockridge Station. We are very near the University of California at Berkeley campus (15 min.) and major highways 80, 580, 24 and 880, which can whisk you to the vibrant galleries of Sausalito (40 minutes), San Jose (50 minutes), or Santa Cruz (90 minutes). If you are up for a day-long outing, don't miss the grand Muir Woods, wine tours in Napa, or mud baths in
host_about: Artist and interior designer based  in San Francisco and Los Angeles. Lover of traveling and experiencing new adventures. Addicted to Bali - been there 8 times and counting. Most recently, I have invested my time into healing and wellness. That said, I have created a Japanese Tatami Room, which I call: Kuro Neko (Black Cat). Kuro Neko is for mindfulness and identity building. By leveraging education, yoga, tea ceremonies, and other ancient practices, I want to create a community of overall well-being and creativity. Looking forward to hosting and traveling using airbnb!

neighborhood_overview: A stylish, modern and bright cottage in the lower Maxwell Park neighborhood. This private and peaceful studio is located in the back garden, removed from the street. name: Guesthouse in Oakland · *4.86 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
San Francisco is an 18 minute drive away, there’s a bus stop right outside the door that will take you to the train station and hop on a train from there. Berkeley is a 15 minute drive away, there are quite a few hiking trails within a 10 minute radius! Endless food options are within walking distance. The Laurel up and coming food options such as Degrees Plato Tap House, Sequoia Diner and 4505 BQQ are minutes away. Tacos in the Fruitvale district a few blocks away are highly recommended (best in California).

Bear in mind that this house is in a culturally diverse urban location where houses are very close to each other and the main street can get busy during peak hours. Plenty of off-street parking available.
host_about: We're a couple who enjoy traveling, hiking, socializing, and good food. Always in search of the best hiking trails and love spending time outdoors.

neighborhood_overview: The airbnb is located in West Oakland which is about as centrally located as you can get! It is definetily a neighborhood and therefore is quiet and has great weather especially compared to SF.  The neighborhood is a mix of redone Victorians, new condos and apartments, as well as some up and coming areas.  Please note there are people of all different socioeconomic classes in both Oakland and in SF, so please be aware that although there are many young families and professionals, there are also those that are less fortunate.
host_about:
Born and raised just north of San Francisco, I am a native that loves the entire Bay Area. Being so close to San Francisco is so much fun, but living in Oakland is amazing and I would love to share both of my cities with you! 

I have worked in hospitality for many years and it is one of my passions, so if you need recommendations for the best the area has to offer, please just ask!

I also work from home now so I’m available if you have any needs during your stay, although your space and privacy is always a priority and you can have an entirely contactless stay if you prefer.

name: Rental unit in Oakland · *4.41 · 2 bedrooms · 3 beds · 1 bath
host_about:
I'm a mid-30's Airbnb Host and Traveler with over a decade in the SF Bay Area, ready to help you find a great home for your short or 1+ month stay. I'm also honored to have over 250 great reviews on Airbnb. While we accept shorter reservations, we specialize in providing furnished homes for 1-12 months, and have noticed many of our customers are business travelers and travel nurses. And we know what they want!

Safe homes with amenities and transportation nearby, close to work, good office chair & desk for working at home, easy check-in without coordinating schedules, large WiFi connected TV's with Netflix to relax, personalized recommendations to meet like-minded folks, access to outdoor and fitness areas... and plenty more. As a former employee traveling for work in the finance industry, I realized that staying in hotels for long periods wasn't all it was chalked up to be... and that I could help provide a better experience for other travelers also. 

I've hosted hundreds of guests from around the US and world, and have studios to 2 bedroom apartments around the San Francisco Bay Area and Silicon Valley: 
- Mountain View
- San Jose
- Redwood City
- Oakland (quick commute to San Francisco)
- Richmond

Send me a message and let's see what we can find closest to your work that meets your needs.

I LOVE the San Francisco Bay Area, and I want you to also! I've lived here for over a decade, and there may be no other place in the world that offers the mix of opportunity, great weather, beautiful nature, urban activities, events, concerts, sporting events, and all kinds of great people.

I'll provide you my own local guide of activities, meetups for your personal interests, and do my best to enjoying your time in the Bay, being productive, staying active, and making the most of your time here (or you're welcome to relax.. we're just here when you need us.)

I have personally stayed in over 25 different Airbnb apartments around the US and the world, so I also know a thing or two about what makes a great furnished home and host. And will do my best to provide that to you. 

A little more about me personally: I've lived in California my whole life, and graduated from San Francisco State University, with a major in Economics and minor in Finance. I've lived all over the Bay Area, including most of the homes I host on Airbnb. I used to work for the State of California in bank regulation, before providing furnished homes and great stays to my guests full-time. 

I enjoy learning and sharing with other Airbnb hosts and real estate investors. In my free time, I also enjoy water color painting, karaoke, beaches, traveling, and making people happy :) 

I realize the San Francisco Bay Area gets very busy and can be quite pricey relative to other locations, so please send me a message so I can see what affordable home we can get you, before everything gets booked up. Thank you for your time.

Enjoy cycling, reading, exploring wine regions, tech and sunshine.

name: Rental unit in Oakland · *4.80 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview:
Grand/Lakeshore is the best that Oakland has to offer! This traditional neighborhood has gone through a revival, like its neighbors in Uptown and Temescal, but nothing beats its proximity to Lake Merritt, the famous Saturday farmer's market, and the iconic Grand Lake Theater.

This is a highly walkable neighborhood, with dozens of nearby restaurants and bars. Safeway is on the corner, as well as famous Zachary's Pizza. The Morcom Rose Garden is also around the corner and very worthy of a visit.

For those who like longer walks, the hills of Piedmont lie just outside your doorstep for endless exploration of beautiful and pristine neighborhoods and parks.

host_about: I'm a dance teacher specializing in working with dance phobic people who can't learn from anyone else.  I'm passionate about teaching and spreading the joy of dance, especially partner dance.  I also collect rare plants and have a beautiful and interesting (if a tad unruly) garden, which I tend to all by myself, hence the unruly part.  I love to cook, but my diet is pretty basic, mostly plants, simply prepared with very little processed foods.  I'm a good conversationalist, but my schedule is erratic, so no guarantee I'll be around when you want to talk.  Happy to supply you with all the info you want about the area!  I can't live without good friends, integrity, laughter, dancing, new things to try, and nature.  When I travel, it's usually dance related, although I did achieve my dream of an English country garden tour a few years ago.   I spent the month of July in Sweden and Norway for 8 years studying a European jazz dance (boogie woogie) that I fell in love with.  My home is a quiet space, good for people who want to rest when they get back to their room, not good for people who want to party in their room, rather than on the town. (Also not good for smokers.  Please see house rules if you smoke.)

name: Guesthouse in Oakland · *5.0 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Much of Oakland's charm in my opinion is in its ethnic, race, class and political diversity, and the vibrant San Antonio district is a classic representation of this cross-section. My neighbors come from many parts of the world but we share food, fruit, and greetings while we walk our dogs and kids up the block. The street is tucked up on a hill away from the major thoroughfares, with sun and breeze and views of the Bay sparkling to the west and the city skyline to the north - but it's under 2 miles from downtown Oakland with its off -the-hook restaurant and club scene, street life, and BART connection to the broader Bay.
Coming home from the bustling, challenging city I love feels like returning to an oasis of calm and peace. You're welcomed to join us there!
host_about: I am a health care provider and an avid outdoorswoman.  Since moving to the Bay Area I have enjoyed rowing crew on Lake Merritt, cycling the network of bike-friendly roads in the Bay Area, hiking and running with my 2 viszla dogs, and backpacking in the Sierra and elsewhere.  I also very much enjoy sustainable organic gardening and trail maintenance.  I totally groove on cultural exchange.  For me, running this inn is a natural outgrowth of being a returned Peace Corps Volunteer (Ivory Coast, '97-99), speaking Spanish, French and German, and always looking for the most realistic and genuine reflection of a community when I travel abroad. I hope to reflect the best of Oakland to my guests, while learning some about the world from my guests and their experiences.

name: Home in Oakland · *4.75 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath
neighborhood_overview: Glenview is a great walking neighborhood.    There's a merchant strip on Park Blvd that's about 1/2 mile away, another merchant strip on Fruitvale about 1 mile away, and Lakeshore about 1.5 miles away.  Highland Hospital is less than 1 mile away.  Other medical centers (Kaiser, Summit) are about 3 miles away.  We are 2 miles from Lake Merritt, and 3 miles to downtown Oakland.
host_about:

name: Bungalow in Oakland · *4.66 · 3 bedrooms · 3 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview: Maxwell Park is a well kept secret in close proximity to San Francisco. Community, diversity, history, story book homes and great views in some parts define it. It is a collection of magnificent California Bungalows with tons of individuality built in the 1920s. It is where neighbors walk up and greet each other and look out for one another. The most famous denizen of Maxwell Park was surely Bruce Lee, of international martial arts and moviemaking fame. In 1964, he drove from Seattle to the Maxwell Park home of local Kung Fu master James Yimm Lee. There, in the garage of 3039 Monticello Ave., was James’ martial arts studio. Oakland has also been home to several famous artists and celebrities giving it a rich heritage in arts, music , food trends and culture. Think Vice President Kamala Harris, think Oakland Walk of Fame and the music they played, think Impossible Burger, think Vegan Food, think sustainability and social justice, think Black Panther and think the Oscar winning Moonlight

And for those who love the outdoors, Lake Merritt and Oakland Redwood Regional Park are just a short 10-minute drive away, where you can take in the breathtaking natural beauty of Northern California.

Our charming neighborhood boasts a lively community of healthy food groceries stores, coffee shops, restaurants, and local activities that will captivate you throughout your stay. name: Rental unit in Oakland · *4.88 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
The neighborhood Longfellow is known for its cultural and racial diversity. Easy access to all highways; going to San Francisco, uptown Oakland and virtually the entire Bay Area is very easy. It’s often described as “up and coming urban”. Please feel free to research Longfellow Oakland before your arrival. There’s a buzzing scene of new development and trendy shops around the neighborhood, where we are tucked in a quiet residential street with “painted Ladies” looking cute colorful houses on the block.

1.5 block from one of the largest Safeway, 10 minutes walk from Pixar animation Studio, 5 minutes drive to Emeryville shopping/entertainment and restaurants. MacArthur Bart station is 5 blocks away where you can find buzzing scene of new development and trendy shops. We love the Whole Foods at the Lake Merritt, it's one of the finest and largest in the Bay Area. 7 minutes drive to Berkeley Bowl West, which is arguably the best grocery store in the US.
host_about: Jess is a designer, photographer, musician, investor and entrepreneur. She has a big love for nature, art & beauty; when she's not taking care of her guests, she's creating beauty in one of her gardens or design projects. Message me if you need your spaces designed or managed professionally!

The Piedmont Avenue business district runs between MacArthur Boulevard and Pleasant Valley Avenue in Oakland . Block for block, it may be the most interesting and eclectic district in Oakland. There are many wonderful one-of-a-kind shops and restaurants that a simple walk down the avenue does not even begin to reveal. There are also interesting shops just half a block off Piedmont on several side streets. To date, the sprinkling of chain establishments has been easy enough to ignore. name: Condo in Oakland · *4.60 · Studio · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Longfellow is a rapidly gentrifying neighborhood of Oakland full of character buildings and a few diverse characters. Please exercise caution and good judgement as you would in other urban areas dealing with homelessness and urban poverty. As a single woman, I've never felt unsafe here (being on a well-lit main street helps!) but do not expect a quiet suburb either.

For those wanting to check out a few local gems, don't miss Eli's Mile High Club for live jazz and local artists, Wally's for the best middle-eastern (eat at the counter and chat up your neighbor), Subrosa Coffee on MLK, and Hometown Heroes, Kebabery, and Arthur Mac's Tap and Shack!
host_about:
Always up for an adventure, a good book, a great glass of wine, and delectable local cuisine, I'd like to be a global nomad and travel to every part of the world, if I could. At the moment, I run startups in recycling, renewable energy, and curated travel. In fact, it was by listing my home in Somerville (just outside Boston) that I was able to fund my first company. So thank you to all the travelers who've made this dream possible! 

As a host: I'm glad to open up my home in Somerville that I painstakingly renovated and now co-host with my mom (who is in California but much closer than I am!). It's a delightful spot that lets you explore locally (Union Square!) and also make the most of Cambridge and Boston too! A great base for a single person, couples, and families alike. 

As a guest: I will treat your home as if it were my own and would love to get tips on your favourite spots to eat and activities, places, music, and events to explore. If you have books about local history, culture, or even novels you can recommend, I'd love to hear about them and even discuss them over a meal or coffee/tea with you!

host_about:
I currently live in Oakland but originally came from Vietnam with my family in 1981. I grew up in Boston, MA and graduated from Boston University with a Bachelor Degree’s in Finance. After graduation, I moved to the Seattle area for a year but decided to settle in Oakland in 1992, where I raised my two sons, who are now adults.
I enjoy dancing, checking out real estate, skiing, traveling, wine tasting, and listening to live music, or simply cooking for my family and friends. Why cooking? I enjoy hosting a small party because I enjoy setting a pretty table, playing with the lighting and music, stocking the bathroom with cute items, and making my cocktail and dinner menus. These are all a sort of an artistic exercise that I find very satisfying. It’s a lot of work but it’s just very nice to see everyone dolled up and happy. At the end of the party, I feel I’ve contributed my gift to everyone, especially to my family and friends. I consider myself a great cook and a great bartender. One of things I enjoy most to make is seafood; I also love to mix cocktails with fresh herbs before dinner and then serve red wine at dinner. I know seafood is not supposed to pair with red wine but I like drinking red wine with anything. Who wouldn’t like it, right?
Since I am an empty nester and a world traveler, I have always been looking for new places to travel and eat. When I travel whether domestically and internationally or whether staying in a hotel or an Airbnb, I do pay a lot attention to cleanliness and comfort, amenities, and the location of the stay. My utmost priority is a comfortable bed and cleanliness. I don’t smoke. I am very tidy, clean, and respectful with my surroundings. I take my world traveling, dining out, cooking and hosting experience into consideration to provide the ultimate guest experience at my place for you.

Trendy Lakeshore Ave Neigborhood with every city convenience and weekly farmers market. Express bus stop to San Francisco close by.

The Lake Merritt area began to see young professionals flock to its borders when San Francisco rents began skyrocketing, and it’s easy to see why they came here. The city of Oakland invested millions of dollars in cleaning up the lake, which was once a dirty, swampy eye-sore, and now groups of young people can be seen picnicking on the manicured grass while families stroll along the waterfront. The lake and its 3.4-mile shoreline also provide residents with a place for outdoor activities like biking rowing, jogging, and walking the dog.

A large concentration of the neighborhood’s bars, restaurants, and entertainment can be found along Grand Avenue–and you won’t have trouble remembering their names. neighborhood_overview:
Once a shopping district in the early 20th century, Uptown is the hottest neighborhood in Oakland with nearly 125 restaurant, bars and boutiques opened in the past decade. Billed as the arts and entertainment district of Oakland, it fulfills its promise, particularly during the boisterous Art Murmur on First Fridays. But the prettiest art may be the Art Deco buildings themselves, with the crown jewels being the show stopping Fox and the Paramount theaters. The former is mostly a live music venue; the latter channels its inner flapper often (classic movies with a live organ player). Art galleries, run by the artists or by volunteers, are opening in brick warehouses. Down side streets are scenes of the start-up, DIY revolution with co-ops, an urban winery, entrepreneur hubs, and creative centers.


Other Things To Do...
Tucked away on 26th street, Classic Cars West is home to a vintage and classic car sales and consignment, on site vegan restaurant and beer garden.

neighborhood_overview:
East Oakland has a mixed feel of the urban vibes. The neighborhood is very safe, though some of the surrounding streets may feel a bit gritty. You will see a mix of graffiti, well maintained homes, neglected homes, industrial buildings, trains, and greeting dogs. Some travelers feel comfortable walking or jogging around the neighborhood as others prefer using uber/lyft/taxi. As we would in any city, we exercise caution and maintain awareness of our surroundings and we suggest that to guests. Experienced and confident travelers who like exposure to different cultures tend to love our neighborhood. If you are looking for a silent suburban feel this may not be the best place for you. Being centrally located and having a clean, high quality suite are just some of the many reasons why this may be the perfect place for you!

Take a lyft to Fruitvale BART and head on to San Francisco in less than 20 minutes! 
Explore or restore, our little tiny home is neat and cheerful.

Thank you for reading- we look forward to making your stay as comfortable, informed, and respected as possible!


We hope you love the fun pops of color and charming style we have blended to make this space special! 

Just to clarify: your entry will be semi-private in that you will pass our main house as you make your way to the cottage! We have a gated entry with a code and several gated yards. You will be able to privately enter and depart as you please!

The Weather Is Great, Tending Towards Cool Evenings With Some Fog (It's Warmer And Less Foggy Than Much Of San Francisco, And Much More Temperate Than Just Over The Hills Towards Walnut Creek).

Please Note There Are People Of All Different Socioeconomic Classes In Both Oakland And In SF, So Please Be Aware That Although There Are Many Young Families And Professionals, There Are Also Those Who Are Less Fortunate.

Home Is Just One BART Stop (10 Min Ride From Lake Merrit Station) To Embarcadero/Downtown San Francisco. Quickly Get To Events, Venues, Conference Centers & Restaurants, All Over The Bay Area!
host_about: Amy Qiong Xian: San Francisco Bay area resident Amy has worked in the hospitality industry for decades.  She has worked in hotel and luxury residence services.  Amy has owned this home for over 20 years, and she raised a family here.  Her son is off to medical school and she's happy let others experience her home through Airbnb.  She has also owned her own business (esthetician) and provides personal services for the elderly.  Amy has traveled the World extensively.

name: Rental unit in Oakland · *4.69 · 3 bedrooms · 3 beds · 1 bath
Guesthouse in Oakland · *4.92 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Temescal, one of the city's oldest and most storied neighborhoods, is a vibrant community of artists, shop owners and restauranteurs. Full of innovative and diverse people creating small independent thoughtfully-curated shops and services, you won't have trouble finding amazing food, nightlife, or shopping wherever you look! Check out my guidebook for some local recommendations!

On the other side of Temescal is Piedmont Avenue - one long badass sidewalk of restaurants, shops and homewares, stacked side by side, with nearly nothing vacant. Choices range from family-friendly, 1894-founded Fentons Creamery, which made a cameo in Pixar’s Up, and the Michelin-starred Commis (2009).
host_about:
Food lovers and travel obsessors, whether we’re working or playing, we always give it 100%.

Having stayed at over 50 airbnbs and 100s of hotels worldwide, hospitality is our passion. We aim to bring the best service, comfort and experience to our guests. We truly love thinking about how to make our guests's stay more magical!

We believe in treating people with kindness and love, serving others and paying it forward.

As mental health advocates, we’re also passionate about making an impact by changing the lives of those affected by the illness. We dedicate a portion of our hosting income towards supporting mental health organizations and veterans.

North Oakland is bordered by Downtown Oakland, Oakland Hills, and the adjacent cities of Berkeley, Emeryville and Piedmont. A short 15-minute drive across the Bay Bridge takes you into Downtown San Francisco.

Highlights of the neighborhood include the Temescal district with its many popular restaurants and local shops. The Emeryville Marina and Bay Street Shopping Center are nearby and worth checking out. There are a variety of parks nearby including Bushrod Park, Temescal Creek Park and Doyle Hollis Park among others.

The Lake Merritt districts of Grand Lake and Lake Shore with their many restaurants, shops and the oldest children's amusement park (Fairyland) are also easily accessible.

neighborhood_overview:
West Oakland is lined with condominiums and new and established businesses. Several of the surrounding warehouses serve as artist studios. Most notably the former facilities for American Steel are now Big Art Studios, a unique facility for large-scale artists. Several pieces of work by the constituent art groups within can be found on display outside the complex. Mandela Gateway, a mixed retail and residential development at the south end of Mandela Parkway, surrounds the West Oakland BART station. The old Victorian houses are being refurbished, and new condominium, townhouse, and live-work loft residences have sprung up making for a lively walk around the neighborhood.

name: Guest suite in Oakland · *4.98 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Our house is one block from College Avenue and within a short walk to the Rockridge Bay Area Rapid Transit (BART) line. This allows easy access to San Francisco as well as San Francisco International and the Oakland International Airports.

Rockridge is a residential area of Oakland primarily developed between 1900 to 1940. College Avenue is the main commercial street that connects two colleges: the California College of Art on Broadway to the south and the University of California in Berkeley to the north. (The CCA buildings are presently being repurposed after the school moved to San Francisco). Along College Avenue you will find restaurants, cafes, bookstores, grocery stores, nail and hair salons, as well as a miscellany of other small retail businesses.

neighborhood_overview:
Cleveland Heights neighborhood is located in Alameda County (Oakland) and is one of the best places to live, and top places to visit in California. Living in Cleveland Heights offers residents a European feel and is both just far enough away to be a peaceful sanctuary and escape, but can quickly get to the action, music, events and more in Oakland, Berkeley, San Francisco and everywhere else in the Bay Area.

You'll also find that Cleveland Heights has a lot of restaurants, coffee shops, bars, an out of this world Taco Truck (Mi Ranchero) and some great parks (Including a Redwood Tree Regional park, nearby).

Lake Merritt is steps from your Airbnb, and you can usually find a variety of vendors and people. The weather is usually great, is cool in the morning and warm in the afternoon.

If you are not familiar with large American cities please do your research on crime and safety when traveling to San Francisco and Oakland.

Follow the stairs of Eucalyptus Path 10 minutes down to the restaurants, cafes and spa at the historic 5-star Claremont Hotel (or take the more meandering Evergreen Path if the stairs are too steep)! name: Home in Oakland · *4.65 · 3 bedrooms · 3 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Nestled in the heart of one of Oakland's most established and secure neighborhoods, our home is situated in a mature, walkable community. Families often relish leisurely strolls, taking in scenic views that define the charm of this well-established locale in the Oakland Hills. Enjoy the safety and tranquility of this neighborhood, surrounded by lush landscapes.

Conveniently located, our home provides easy access to the beauty of Lake Merritt, the serene surroundings of Lake Chabot, and the adventurous trails of Joaquin Miller Park, perfect for mountain biking and hiking enthusiasts. Explore the vibrant energy of Jack London Square and the cultural richness of downtown Oakland, all within close proximity. Immerse yourself in the diverse offerings of this mature and inviting neighborhood."
host_about: As avid travelers ourselves, we understand the transformative power of a memorable journey and the significance of finding a home away from home. Our wanderlust has taken us to diverse corners of the world, allowing us to appreciate the warmth and hospitality of unique accommodations. Now, we are thrilled to open the doors of our own beautiful space to fellow travelers, inviting you to experience the charm and tranquility that defines our home.

name: Guest suite in Oakland · *4.95 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Current:
McClymonds is a mixed-use neighborhood in West Oakland named for McClymonds High School. West Oakland is bordered by North Oakland, Downtown Oakland, Oakland Hills, and the adjacent cities of Berkeley, Emeryville and Piedmont. A short 15-minute drive across the Bay Bridge takes you into Downtown San Francisco.

Highlights of the neighborhood include the Temescal district with its many popular restaurants and local shops. The Emeryville Marina, Bay Street Shopping Center, Old Oakland Shopping District, and Chinatown are nearby and worth checking out (all within 10 min drive). The Lake Merritt districts of Grand Lake and Lake Shore with their many restaurants, shops and the oldest children's amusement park, Fairyland (5 min drive), are also easily accessible.

name: Rental unit in Oakland · *4.71 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
This is the neighborhood to be in if you want diversity, urban, city life, convenience, and if you're a foodie!

The apartment is located on the border of Temescal and Lower Rockridge. One block to Kingfish Pub, 1.5 blocks from the weekly Temescal Farmers Market, two blocks to Bakesale Betty's on the corner, Rockridge Bart is a 5 minute bike ride away, as well as the Macarthur Bart! You have all of Rockridge and Temescal at walking distance of 5 to 15 minutes.

Neighborhood is considered part of the NOBE district which stands for North Oakland Berkeley Emeryville. The apartment is located in a neighborhood that has been transforming for many years. Since the pandemic, the city has had a large problem with transients and homelessness. So it isn't uncommon to see tents under freeways nearby or just all over the city. If you aren't comfortable seeing this, staying here may not be the right fit for you.

name: Rental unit in Oakland · *4.90 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Oakland was recently voted one of the 10 most interesting cities to visit in the US by The Traveler magazine. It has become one of the youngest cities in all California. Young professionals prefer it not only because is substantially less expensive than our famous neighboring city, but also because it offers the most flavorful array of entertainment and eateries of the entire area at a fraction of what your pay across the Bay.

In terms of the neighborhood where your flat is located, true diversity is the first phrase that comes to mind when trying to define “Clinton District” (name of this section of town). People of different ethnicities, backgrounds and ages coexist peacefully. It’s only 7 blocks away from the crown joule of the city, the Lake Merritt, a place with magnificent views and architecture were Oaklanders gather for farmers’ market, strolling, salsa-dancing, acro-yoga, jogging, celebrating life, etc.

Around the Lake there are plenty of coffee shops

name: Home in Oakland · *5.0 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Santa Fe is a hidden gem off-the-beaten-track neighborhood hosting creatives, cooperatives, verdant gardens, and vintage homes.  It's walking distance to Rockridge and Temescal, and easy access to UC Berkeley and San Francisco. Check out the guidebook to the neighborhood or ask for specific recommendations anytime.

name: Rental unit in Oakland · *4.95 · 1 bedroom · 3 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: There are plenty of dining options in Forestland, Oakland. You can grab your morning cup of coffee from Grand Lake Kitchen, Peet's Coffee & Tea, or Sophie's Cuppa Tea and sit down for a relaxed weekend brunch at House Of Bagels, Sequoia Diner, or Chabot Space & Science Center. Dessert shops like Batch Pastries, Star Grocery, and The Pasta Shop are great options for satifying your sweet tooth. Residents love to order tacos from El Agavero Mexican Restaurant & Bar, Nido, or CHICA Oakland and burgers from Sparky's Giant Burgers, TrueBurger, or pattys and buns. Casa Orinda, Daughter Thai, or TrueBurger are some great spots for a fun dine-in experience. We also have quite a few grocery stores including Village Market Oakland, The Food Mill, and Whole Foods Market.
