You will see a mix of graffiti, well maintained homes, neglected homes, industrial buildings, trains, and greeting dogs. Some travelers feel comfortable walking or jogging around the neighborhood as others prefer using uber/lyft/taxi. As we would in any city, we exercise caution and maintain awareness of our surroundings and we suggest that to guests. Experienced and confident travelers who like exposure to different cultures tend to love our neighborhood. If you are looking for a silent suburban feel this may not be the best place for you. Being centrally located and having a clean, high quality home are just some of the many reasons why this may be the perfect place for you!

name: Condo in Oakland · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview: Once a shopping district in the early 20th century, Uptown is the hottest neighborhood in Oakland. A new restaurant, indie boutique, or bar seemingly opens every other week, with nearly 125 opened in the past decade. Billed as the arts and entertainment district of Oakland, it fulfills its promise, particularly during the boisterous Art Murmur on First Fridays. But the prettiest art may be the Art Deco buildings themselves, with the crown jewels being the show stopping Fox and the Paramount theaters. The former is mostly a live music venue; the latter channels its inner flapper often (classic movies with a live organ player). Art galleries, run by the artists or by volunteers, are opening in brick warehouses. Down side streets are scenes of the start-up, DIY revolution with co-ops, an urban winery, entrepreneur hubs, and creative centers.

name: Rental unit in Oakland · *5.0 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath

Working-class neighborhood. Quiet street with a school at the end of it. Near RedBay Coffee a gourmet coffee bar & roaster. Much good food from Mexico & Central America within walking distance 5-10 minutes.

Our home is located on a cul-de-sac street in the Fruitvale district. This is a residential area near commercial streets with lots of restaurants, and near many artist live/work spaces. Like other developing Oakland neighborhoods, Fruitvale has a lot of contrast. Celebrated for its diversity, it is home to a large immigrant population (predominantly Spanish-speaking) and to working-class families and these days people are paying $800k for a 1,000 square foot condo here. We are 0.9 miles to the Fruitvale BART station and the new bus rapid transit line. There are restaurants, a gas station, grocery stores, and laundry just around the corner. We are a short drive to the Oakland hills and the Alameda estuary and shoreline.

Fruitvale is home to people from all walks

Hi there!

I'll be your host during your stay. :) I live next door to my airbnb listing,  so I'm there to help if you need anything.

I am a planner. I like to prepare ahead of time to ensure you have a great experience arriving at my home, during your stay, and when you head home.

If I'm not hosting you, then you may be hosting me! I love to travel!

Well...  I keep spaces clean and tidy. Usually sleep at 10:30pm or 11pm. I wake up around 7am and I work remotely from 8:30am to 6pm Pacific time for my employer. I often work remotely while traveling. 

I don't smoke. I don't own pets.  I'm a digital marketer by trade. Originally, I am from Berkeley, CA. Anything else you want to know, just ask!

name: Home in Oakland · *5.0 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Oakland’s Bushrod neighborhood is known for its convenient location, charming homes, and its proximity to restaurants and stores. The neighborhood’s incredibly convenient location is next to Rockridge, Temescal, blocks from the Berkeley Farmers Market and near three BART stations.

Throughout the tree lined streets, you'll find a variety of craftsman, bungalows, and even storybook homes (in Idora park). A lot of these charming homes were built in the early 1900s and have kept their original characteristics, while some have been renovated for a more modern feel.

In 2017, the real estate firm Redfin name Bushrod the hottest neighborhood market in the United States based on traffic to its website by potential home buyers.
host_about: Hi! I'm an Oakland based Designer, avid traveler and corgi lover.  My partner and I bought the craftsman bungalow of our dreams last year and share it whenever we travel. The Berkeley Bowl is a popular spot in town. It is a grand organic supermarket that has an expansive produce section. Since it is within close proximity of the University of California, Berkeley, it is a popular neighborhood to live for students that want an easy commute to their classes. It is not only popular to students however, the town is welcoming to all young adults, families, and elders. For this reason, there is a diverse demographic living in South Berkeley.

For restaurants and bars, the residents of South Berkeley recommend the quick trip into Downtown. That is where most of the highly rated eateries reside, and it is never a hassle to get there. name: Rental unit in Oakland · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath

neighborhood_overview:
The happening Laurel District is the "middle of the middle" of Oakland. At the junction of the hills and the flats it is a diverse mix of all that is great about the city with a range of class, race and sexuality. The census shows it as 1/3 black, 1/3 asian and 1/3 white. Known for peaceful and happy co-existence, it is a warm and friendly place for all comers.

The house is at the bottom of a hill on a cul de sac. Because there is little traffic on the hill, because it has bay views at the top and because of the exercise challenge (it's very steep!) the street attracts walkers, runners, professional athletes (such as the Oakland As), rugged cyclists and even one brave monocyclist!

There are also plenty of flat neighborhood streets for sauntering and dog walking.

It's 6 minutes walk to main street where you will find a range of eateries, include barbecue, thai, cambodian, breakfast and mexican. Bars, food shops, pharmacies, a gym, a hardware store, cl
host_about: Hey! I'm a landscaper, writer, artist, cook, grower of food and keeper of chickens. I love nature, backpacking with friends, long walks with my dog and trips to beautiful places. I am a gay man and proud dad of two fine sons.

name: Guesthouse in Oakland · *5.0 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Oakland's Rockridge is a delightfully walkable neighborhood of quiet residential streets which ranges along College Avenue and up into the lower slopes of the Oakland Hills. Two vibrant commercial districts of small specialty shops and restaurants enliven the three miles of College Avenue between its start at Oakland's Broadway and its northern terminus at the UC Berkeley campus: our local commercial district is anchored by the Rockridge BART station and the Rockridge Market Hall, a European-styled complex which features a full range of fine food vendors and beverage shops. Dining options within minutes' walk from our door include a wide range of fast casual, ethnic and fine dining establishments. Midway to UC, Berkeley's Elmwood district offers more interesting shopping and a slightly more casual range of cafes and restaurants.

Oakland was recently voted one of the 10 most interesting cities to visit in the US by The Traveler magazine. It has become one of the youngest cities in all California. Young professionals prefer it not only because is substantially less expensive than our famous neighboring city, but also because it offers the most flavorful array of entertainment and eateries of the entire area at a fraction of what your pay across the Bay.
In terms of the neighborhood where your studio is located, true diversity is the first phrase that comes to mind when trying to define “Fruitvale District” (name of this section of town). People of different ethnicities, backgrounds and ages coexist peacefully. It’s only a short drive/bike or an economical uber-ride from the crown joule of the city, the Lake Merritt, a place with magnificent views and architecture were Oaklanders gather for farmers’ market, strolling, salsa-dancing, acro-yoga, jogging, celebrating life, etc.

It has become one of the youngest cities in all California. In terms of the neighborhood where your home is located, true diversity is the first phrase that comes to mind when trying to define “Fruitvale District” (name of this section of town). People of different ethnicities, backgrounds and ages coexist peacefully. neighborhood_overview: A nice, cute residential suburb very central to many things! There's an elementary school and public park across the street, as well as a row of Palm Trees to welcome you to California. From this neighborhood, there are many sightseeing areas to view the San Francisco skyline just a walk away. Within a 1-mile radius, you have a handful of dining options: from mom-and-pop authentic restaurants (e.g., Champa Garden thai food, Cam Huong vietnamese sandwiches, Pho Ao Sen vietnamese noodles, variety of Mexican food trucks) to adorable coffee shops (e.g., Arizmendi Bakery, Xochi The Dog Cafe, Rise & Grind Coffee, Haddon Hill Cafe). And if these options don't suit you, going to Downtown Oakland is just one bus stop away with the 62 bus right across the street!

name: Rental unit in Oakland · *4.33 · Studio · 1 bed · 1 bath
host_about:
I'm a mid-30's Airbnb Host and Traveler with over a decade in the SF Bay Area, ready to help you find a great home for your short or 1+ month stay. I'm also honored to have over 250 great reviews on Airbnb. While we accept shorter reservations, we specialize in providing furnished homes for 1-12 months, and have noticed many of our customers are business travelers and travel nurses. And we know what they want!

Safe homes with amenities and transportation nearby, close to work, good office chair & desk for working at home, easy check-in without coordinating schedules, large WiFi connected TV's with Netflix to relax, personalized recommendations to meet like-minded folks, access to outdoor and fitness areas... and plenty more. As a former employee traveling for work in the finance industry, I realized that staying in hotels for long periods wasn't all it was chalked up to be... and that I could help provide a better experience for other travelers also. 

I've hosted hundreds of guests from around the US and world, and have studios to 2 bedroom apartments around the San Francisco Bay Area and Silicon Valley: 
- Mountain View
- San Jose
- Redwood City
- Oakland (quick commute to San Francisco)
- Richmond

Send me a message and let's see what we can find closest to your work that meets your needs.

I LOVE the San Francisco Bay Area, and I want you to also! I've lived here for over a decade, and there may be no other place in the world that offers the mix of opportunity, great weather, beautiful nature, urban activities, events, concerts, sporting events, and all kinds of great people.

I'll provide you my own local guide of activities, meetups for your personal interests, and do my best to enjoying your time in the Bay, being productive, staying active, and making the most of your time here (or you're welcome to relax.. we're just here when you need us.)

I have personally stayed in over 25 different Airbnb apartments around the US and the world, so I also know a thing or two about what makes a great furnished home and host. And will do my best to provide that to you. 

A little more about me personally: I've lived in California my whole life, and graduated from San Francisco State University, with a major in Economics and minor in Finance. I've lived all over the Bay Area, including most of the homes I host on Airbnb. I used to work for the State of California in bank regulation, before providing furnished homes and great stays to my guests full-time. 

I enjoy learning and sharing with other Airbnb hosts and real estate investors. In my free time, I also enjoy water color painting, karaoke, beaches, traveling, and making people happy :) 

I realize the San Francisco Bay Area gets very busy and can be quite pricey relative to other locations, so please send me a message so I can see what affordable home we can get you, before everything gets booked up. Thank you for your time.

name: Loft in Oakland · *5.0 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview:
This is THE PLACE for incredible independent artists' open studios which happen often. There's a pristine boardwalk that's beautifully manicured along the estuary for walks, picnicking, walking a dog, or just watching the birds and reading a book.

Across the estuary is the island of Alameda which has brew pubs, great restaurants, and my favorite- over 3 miles of beach! Many people swim, windsurf, and exercise on this sandy stretch and the sunsets are unbelievable! There are many parks and a handful of yacht clubs as well as many little neighborhood retail areas to explore.

Down the Embarcadero which you can either walk, drive, or better yet- ride a bike is the new Brooklyn Basin- an open space park where you'll find a diverse group of people roller skating, celebrating birthday parties, and grabbing something to eat from the special grocery/cafe on site. Further down a few blocks is Jack London Square which is bustling with people enjoying a movie, all of the res

Love the beach/ocean/sailing.

name: Guest suite in Oakland · *5.0 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Located in exclusive Montclair neighborhood in Bay Area. Close to restaurants, schools, arts and entrainment. Huckleberry Botanica Regional Preserve and Sibley Volcanic Regional Preserve are few hundred feet away for hiking or biking. A unique urban and forestry location combined. Off Highway 13, this neighborhood has some of the most popular real estates in the Bay Area, with a pedestrian-friendly Montclair village which has a Bavarian mountain town feel to it. Montclair is the gateway into Oakland’s wilderness parks (Redwood Regional and Joaquin Miller) with some of the East Bay’s best hiking and biking spots nearby. There is also Chabot Space & Science Center close in the hills. A beautiful upscale neighborhood with amazing views, climate and culture.
host_about: I have lived in Oakland Hills for over 25 years. Enjoying living in such a beautiful, serene and peaceful location. I am around to check you in personally.

This location is situated in the heart of Oakland, one of the most diverse and exciting cities in the San Francisco Bay Area.

The neighborhood is known for its unique blend of historic architecture, lively cultural scene, and excellent dining and shopping options. You can explore the area on foot and find everything from vintage shops and artisanal food markets to trendy bars and music venues.

If you're a foodie, you're in luck – this area is known for its fantastic food scene. You can find everything from classic soul food and barbecue to trendy fusion restaurants and cafes that cater to vegans and vegetarians. The nearby Jack London Square is also a great place to grab a drink, take in some live music, or catch a movie.

name: Home in Oakland · *5.0 · 2 bedrooms · 3 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview:
Our address has a walk score of 92 (“Walker’s Paradise”) with Whole Foods (7 minutes), Safeway (10 minutes) and Trader Joe's (15 minutes) all nearby.

Our location in the popular Rockridge district just next to trendy Temescal gives guests an array of shops and lively restaurants and bars within walking distance:
- 9 minutes west to Temescal Alley/Burma Superstar,
- 8 minutes east to College Ave’s award-winning Marica seafood restaurant and the start of a 6-block stroll past a variety of tempting ethnic eateries.

Rockridge is a bonanza for fans of Craftsman architecture (1900-1930) - make sure to set aside time during your stay to wander around the neighboring streets where longtime residents have lovingly preserved and personalized their architectural heritage.

name: Guesthouse in Oakland · *4.85 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Maxwell Park is a neighborhood located in the foothills of the city, and it is geographically bordered by MacArthur Boulevard, High Street, and Mills College, among others. It lies at an elevation of 138 feet to its highest point of 266 feet on Knowland Ave (42 m)--with amazing views and elevation ideal for hiking!
The neighborhood has a lot of rich history. Its namesake community park sits just around the corner from where martial arts icon Bruce Lee once had a studio. Maxwell Park is also where the mosaic tile trash can trend started.
Warm and inviting, Maxwell Park is a cozy refuge that's an ideal place for families and single young professionals alike trying to escape downtown's rowdiness.
Check out my guidebook for some local recommendations!

Nestled at the foot of the Oakland Hills, with College Ave anchoring this suburban meets European stretch of the East Bay. Here you will find indie bookstores, vintage shopping, home stores, flower shops, food markets and top ranking restaurants filling its sidewalks!
Our house is located just steps away from College Ave. You never know what new delight will be waiting for when you walk outside. Maybe it's a jazz band set up on the corner, or a kid's "farmers market" from the garden. Maybe it's a dance party in the street, or long time neighbors chatting.

Market Hall - A marketplace for curious eaters with a collection of eight owner- operated shops, Rockridge Market Hall is the cornerstone of the neighborhood. Similar to NYC Brooklyn a few years ago. Quickly gentrifying with new houses, new food, new breweries, and great access to all the Bay Area has to offer!

West Oakland’s Prescott neighborhood is centrally located, and just minutes away from 3 major job centers (SF, Oakland, and Emeryville). From West Oakland BART, it’s just 7-minutes to San Francisco’s financial district, 6-minutes to downtown Oakland, and 9-minutes to MacArthur BART near Emeryville. You can’t beat those commute times!
Prescott is also flat, making it very walkeable and bikeable (e.g., it’s about a 10 min bike ride to downtown Oakland). And it’s just a 7–10 minute drive to many awesome Oakland neighborhoods such as Temescal, Jack London Square, and Uptown.

name: Home in Oakland · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 shared bath
Rental unit in Oakland · *4.33 · Studio · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: We're in a neighborhood called Longfellow. It's kind of considered a part of "NOBE" (North Oakland, Berkeley, Emeryville). Since the pandemic, Oakland and much of the Bay Area has had a rise in homelessness and transients. The neighborhood is comprised of diverse working class families and people from all walks of life. The surrounding neighborhood is emerging and urban so we'd only recommend you book if you're comfortable in a big city/urban environment. We have many neighbors, some you'll never see and others that hang out in front of their homes. A little smile and hi go a long way. You'll encounter all sorts of things on the street; hipsters, yupsters, regular Joe's, homeless people, and trash/debris. In other words having STREET SMARTS and being comfortable with diversity are highly recommended. We're often asked about safety when booking or staying in Oakland, and it's not really a question we can answer for you since it's highly subjective. If you're seeking a more suburban feel

name: Rental unit in Oakland · Studio · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: This furnished apartment is located in Oakland, California's eighth largest city. It's also one of the most diverse cities in the US, thanks to a steady wave of immigrants from all over the world during the 20th century. You can experience an impressive range of international cuisine in Oakland, and a fun nightlife scene in general. Oakland is known for its professional sports franchises like the Golden State Warriors and the Oakland Raiders, as well as major health care, manufacturing, and tech companies. The city also serves as a transportation hub for the entire San Francisco Bay Area, making it easy to get around Oakland as well as connect to other cities.
host_about:
We’re Blueground, a global proptech company with several thousand move-in-ready apartments in a growing number of major cities around the world. With flexible terms and homes in vibrant, centrally based neighborhoods, you’ll feel at home and free to roam for as long as you want — a month, a year, or longer. 

Each apartment is thoughtfully designed with exclusive furnishings, fully equipped kitchens, and incredible amenities – making every day a five-star experience. From day one, you’ll enjoy high-speed Wi-Fi, premium linens, and smart home entertainment. Plus, access to pools, gyms, and outdoor spaces in select buildings.

Why stress over your apartment? We provide a hassle-free alternative — a consistent, quality guest experience that starts even before you arrive. Because we let you book our most up-to-date apartment listings online, confirm with a click, pay securely, and check in easily. 

Even better? You can enhance your stay with car rentals, grocery delivery, laundry services, and more through our special partnerships. 

During your stay
Upon arrival, you’ll either be greeted personally by a Blueground team member or given self-check-in instructions. The entire apartment is yours! You’ll enjoy reliable support via email, phone, and our Guest App, where you can request everything from a home cleaning to extra towels. 

We’ll share all details upon confirmation of your stay.

Huckleberry Park and Sibley Parks are few hundred feet away for hiking or biking. A unique urban and forestry location combined. Off Highway 13, this neighborhood has some of the most popular real estates in the Bay Area, with a pedestrian-friendly Montclair village which has a Bavarian mountain town feel to it. Montclair is the gateway into Oakland’s wilderness parks (Redwood Regional and Joaquin Miller) with some of the East Bay’s best hiking and biking spots nearby. There is also Chabot Space & Science Center close in the hills. A beautiful upscale neighborhood with amazing views, climate and culture.

neighborhood_overview:
Maxwell Park is a neighborhood located in the city's foothills, and it is geographically bordered by MacArthur Boulevard, High Street, and Mills College, among others. It lies at an elevation of 138 feet to its highest point of 266 feet on Knowland Ave (42 m)--with amazing views and elevation ideal for hiking!
The neighborhood has a lot of rich history. Its namesake community park sits just around the corner from where martial arts icon Bruce Lee once had a studio. Maxwell Park is also where the mosaic tile trash can trend started.
Warm and inviting, Maxwell Park is a cozy refuge that's an ideal place for families and single young professionals alike trying to escape downtown's rowdiness.

Welcome to Maxwell Park, a hidden gem in Oakland, known for its friendly community, picturesque streets, and convenient location. This guide will help you explore and enjoy this charming neighborhood during your stay.

Rockridge (College Ave):
At the foot of the Oakland Hills, Rockridge is a lovely burby-like haven where Cal Berkeley grads come to live when they exit their 20s and start yearning for historic cottages, nice gardens, and a 95 walk score. Techies who have newly flown the coop are lucky to nab a place to live in this desirable hub. Even so, all ages come to explore this model main street where two indie bookstores thrive (Pegasus and Diesel). name: Home in Oakland · *5.0 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood is an ever changing urban environment filled with long time residents and families, artists, urban farms, colorful graffiti art and the new wave of both hipsters and techies escaping the higher cost of living in SF. This is the old Jazz and Blues historical neighborhood of Oakland. It is predominantly residential with beautiful old Victorians, many of which are undergoing renovation as there has been a lot of renewed interest in the area recently, and some Industrial parts of the neighborhood. The proximity to BART and convenience this offers to all the tourist attractions and great restaurants / walking areas of the Bay Area is what draws people to this part. Paradise Park is an urban, diverse and centrally located residential neighborhood in East Bay - just across from San Francisco via Bay Bridge. It sits on the border with North Oakland, Berkeley and Emeryville.

The North Oakland/Berkeley/Emeryville neighborhood coveted by professionals, hipsters and families alike for its central location, cultural diversity, great climate and close proximity to UC Berkeley and a short drive to San Francisco.

This rapidly changing area checks all the hipster boxes: cupcakes, local great coffee shops, vegan donuts, a knitting shop, a lovely local beer brewery and underground intimate music concerts venue.

With all the bees, chickens, goats, and organic community gardens here, it should probably be dubbed Oakland Farms.

Oakland's scenic neighborhood of Redwood Heights brings together the best aspects of a suburban community with the convenience and variety of a major metropolitan area.

This area is popular with young families and stable, long-term property owners. Many families move in and stay for generations. The neighborhood has much to do and see in walking distance. The Laurel District down the hill and Lincoln Square just up the hill provide the community with grocery stores, restaurants, breweries, breakfast, and local coffee shops.

I am an experience collector! I've had amazing experiences traveling throughout the world - in Africa, Asia, Europe, and across the United States. As a host in my hometown of Oakland, CA, I am excited to be able to provide a place to stay for guests to explore everything my city and the Bay Area has to offer. 

When traveling, I love finding the best pizza a newly explored town has to offer.  And am always interested in learning about a city's history and culture. When hosting, you can bet I have a list at the ready of the best pizza in town. 

I'm a natural introvert so my tendency when traveling is to keep to myself, although I genuinely enjoy meeting new people and learning about them and their culture. As a host, I prioritize the guest and the level of communication they are comfortable with.

host_about:
Hello – nice to e-meet you!

My wife, Karen, and I hope to have the privilege of hosting you some day soon in our lovely, remodeled, private cottage! 

We are both long-time Bay Area residents. Ernesto has lived in Oakland most of his life and Karen, originally a SoCal native, lived across the bay in San Francisco for more than a decade before moving to Oakland after our recent wedding. 

Karen is a Niners and Giants fan, while Ernesto continues to be a diehard Raiders and A's fan, for better or worse…mostly worse. Luckily, we can both root for our Warriors!

We are both Cal grads and enjoy all of the amenities that the Bay Are has to offer. Like most human beings, we love traveling, eating great food, and spending time with our friends and family.

name: Home in Oakland · Studio · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Located in the heart of the city, Uptown Oakland is known for its rich cultural heritage, diverse communities, and bustling nightlife.

Take a stroll down the historic 19th St and visit the many unique shops, boutiques, and cafes. Indulge in the local cuisine and try the famous Oakland-style barbecue or sample the delicious street food at one of the many food trucks.

For culture enthusiasts, Uptown Oakland is a hub of creativity, with a thriving arts and music scene. From the historic Fox Theater, to the contemporary and contemporary galleries, there is something for everyone.

Enjoy a night out at one of the many bars, clubs, and lounges, or catch a live music performance at one of the local venues. Uptown Oakland is also home to several parks and green spaces, making it easy to escape the hustle and bustle of the city.

neighborhood_overview:
The home is located in Rockridge, which is one of Oakland’s oldest and most vibrant shopping/dining areas as well as most sought-after residential communities. Rockridge is ultra-walkable and filled with independent shops, bars, restaurants, cafes, grocery stores, and it's own BART station. Most of these are located on the main thoroughfare of College Avenue - which features classic old architecture on a pedestrian-scale merely 3 blocks from your door.

There is an elementary school at the end of our block, so be prepared to hear the giggles and voices of happy children if you are sitting on the porch/patio during the school hours. Drop off and pickup times create a parade of parents and caretakers walking/biking/driving through.

Super convenient location where you can walk to:

- Bikesharing (Ford Go Bike) station within 2 blocks!

- Cafes, bars/pubs and purveyors of craft cocktails, workout spaces (yoga, pilates, gyms), and independent shops<

name: Guest suite in Oakland · Studio · 2 beds · 1 bath
Serviced apartment in Oakland · *5.0 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Grand Lake aka The Rose Garden was founded in the 1860’s and is a neighborhood made for exploring! Some highlights:
1. The neighborhood is very walkable - we are in the middle of everything! There are sidewalks throughout and lots of interesting streets to explore.
2. The area is an ideal place for runners and cyclists because we are only blocks from Lake Merritt, and not far from the hills for billy-goats.
3. There are TONS of fun restaurants, bars, coffee shops and shops to explore. Please see our Guidebook in the listing for some of our favorite places.
4. The city of Piedmont (not Piedmont Ave., which is actually a neighborhood in Oakland) is about a block from our space and is a great place to explore for those who like architecture. There are some truly spectacular homes there.
5. Our weather is fantastic! The climate is very temperate, with an average annual temperature is 71.5 degrees Fahrenheit. It is much better than many of the surrounding areas -
host_about:
I live and work in Oakland - and love it! I also grew up here, so I am intimately familiar with the area. Please check out the guidebook in the online listing for information on some of my favorite places in the bay area (and beyond). 

Our listing is a side-by-side duplex, and we (my wife and I) live on the other side. As far as our interaction, I can make myself invisible while you are staying at our listing, or if you’d prefer to connect w/ me for any reason I’m happy to do that also. 

I think it’s also worth noting that this our only listing on Airbnb, so we will do everything to make your stay with us a positive experience. If there is anything we can do to make your time more comfortable, just ask! We are not a remote rental mgmt company, nor are we professional airbnb hosts who have 25 listings.

Here you'll be able to explore the city's rich history at attractions like the Oakland Museum of California, the African American Museum and Library, and the USS Potomac, a presidential yacht.

Art lovers will enjoy the city's many galleries and street murals, while foodies can indulge in a wide range of cuisines at numerous restaurants and cafes.

Outdoor enthusiasts can take in the stunning views of the San Francisco Bay from the Oakland Hills or hike through the redwood trees at Redwood Regional Park.

Escape to the tranquility of a quiet Oakland neighborhood for your next vacation! Our peaceful location is the perfect place to unwind and relax. Enjoy the serenity of nature while still being close to all the conveniences of the city.

In the vicinity, there exist diverse options for coffee shops including KilaVolt & Milky Way which can be conveniently accessed within a 10-minute walk. Directly opposite this home, is a private street leading into a senior home. You will find many friendly elderly folks sitting out on the benches socializing and keeping a watch out for our neighbors. This keeps our neighborhood extremely safe.

Couple blocks away is Piedmont Grocery. They are open from 9AM-8PM. CVS is a block after that.

Piedmont Ave is a highly desirable neighborhood. The start of the strip has Kaiser Hospital (5 blocks away) and the end of the strip is the Mountain View Cemetery where many high profile folks are laying to rest (docents offer tours every weekend). In between, you will find shops, convenient stores, bars, Micheline star restaurants, neighborhood cinema, book stores and more.

name: Home in Oakland · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Peralta Hacienda Neighborhood is a historic residential area located in Oakland, California. It is named after the Peralta family, who were early Spanish settlers in the region. The neighborhood is situated near the border of Oakland and San Leandro, and it encompasses the area surrounding the Peralta Hacienda Historical Park.

One of the prominent features of the Peralta Hacienda Neighborhood is the Peralta Hacienda Historical Park, which is a significant cultural and historical landmark. The park is centered around the Peralta Hacienda, a restored adobe house that dates back to the 19th century. The hacienda served as the residence for the Peralta family, who were influential in the early development of the region.

name: Condo in Oakland · 3 bedrooms · 3 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview:
The condo is located in West Oakland, a historically working class neighborhood filled with industrial warehouses, beautiful ornate victorians, and new condo developments. Like any up-and-coming area in a major city, the surroundings can be dirty at times and there can be incidents of crime. Common sense is always encouraged, not just in Oakland, but all major cities like SF; do not leave valuables in your car, if your car has a trunk, leave the seats folded down to show the trunk is empty, pay attention to your surroundings and don't be distracted on your phone.

Several of the surrounding warehouses now serve as artist studios. Most notably the former facilities for American Steel are now a unique facility for large-scale artists, many part of the Burning Man community. Several pieces of work by the constituent art groups within can be found on display outside the complex. Mandela Gateway, a mixed retail and residential development at the south end of Mandela Parkway

name: Rental unit in Oakland · *5.0 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
The Lake Merritt neighborhood in Oakland, California is a vibrant and diverse community situated around the picturesque Lake Merritt, the United States' oldest designated wildlife refuge. Located in the heart of Oakland, this neighborhood offers a unique blend of natural beauty, cultural attractions, and a lively urban atmosphere.

One of the main highlights of the Lake Merritt neighborhood is, of course, Lake Merritt itself. Spanning approximately 155 acres, this urban lake provides a stunning backdrop for outdoor activities and scenic strolls. Visitors can enjoy walking or jogging along the lakeside path, rent paddleboats or kayaks, or simply relax and take in the serene surroundings.

The neighborhood surrounding Lake Merritt is known for its rich cultural and artistic scene. The area is home to several cultural institutions, including the Oakland Museum of California, and a thriving culinary scene.

name: Rental unit in Oakland · *5.0 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Cleveland Heights
Oakland’s Cleveland Heights neighborhood occupies the sloping hills in the northwestern corner of the city’s San Antonio district. Encompassing the historic Haddon Hill and Peralta Heights developments, Cleveland Heights offers hilltop views of the lake and Downtown skyline, surrounded by homes and buildings comprising a variety of early-1900s architectural styles.

Cleveland Heights lies just east of Lake Merritt – residents can take the steep, circa-1920s staircase park of Cleveland Cascade down to the 3.4 miles of waterfront paths and green space. Haddon Hill Café is a neighborhood favorite for coffee and pastries, while nearby Champa Garden serves all types of delicious Asian noodles. Quintessential neighborhood dive Baggy’s by the Lake is a time-honored treasure, and the Lakeshore and Grand Lake shopping districts, each full of bars, restaurants, grocery stores, and other amenities – including the weekly Grand Lake Farmer’s Market – are nearby.

neighborhood_overview:
Old Oakland is a historic district in downtown Oakland, California. The area is located on the northwest side of Broadway, between the City Center complex and the Jack London Square district, and across Broadway from Chinatown.

The Old Oakland district was the "original" downtown Oakland during the 1860s after Central Pacific Railroad constructed a terminus on 7th Street. By the 1870s, elegant brick Victorian hotels were being built in the blocks surrounding the railroad station to accommodate travelers. The ground floor of the hotels were designed as series of narrow shops so that pedestrians would pass by many of them just walking down the block. The architectural styles of the time featured tall, cast-iron columns and large plate-glass windows.

neighborhood_overview:
Resting in a valley formed by the Hayward fault, Montclair sits on the western slope of California‘s Oakland Hills. With heavily-forested winding roads and the quaint center of Montclair village, this Oakland neighborhood is the perfect place to stay in the East Bay.

The Oakland neighborhood of Montclair radiates sweetness from the moment you arrive. Reminiscent of a small ski town, Montclair Village is the heart of this Oakland district. Compactly filled with rows of stores, coffee shops and restaurants, people flock to this commercial area at all hours of the day to enjoy its charming atmosphere. Montclair village is only 5 minutes down the hill from the property.

Like all great neighborhoods near big cities, Oakland has its fair share of crime. This neighborhood isn't known for violent crime but car break-ins and car thefts are possible. Avoid leaving valuables in your car and be aware of your surroundings to avoid being a victim of crime.

neighborhood_overview:
A Quiet Oasis in the Hills

This charming neighborhood is a hidden gem, nestled in the hills just one block from the border of Piedmont. The streets are lined with mostly single-family homes, and there is a sense of peace and quiet that is hard to find in a city.

Residents can easily walk to everything they need, including Safeway, Trader Joe's, Whole Foods, and Lake Merritt. There are also many cool restaurants on Grand Avenue, a hip shopping and walking street at the bottom of the hill. (1 mile radius)

The neighborhood is very safe and friendly. Everyone is always willing to lend a helping hand, and there is plenty of free street parking. However, it is always important to use common sense, especially when walking around at night.

McClymonds is a mixed-use neighborhood in West Oakland named for McClymonds High School. West Oakland is bordered by North Oakland, Downtown Oakland, Oakland Hills, and the adjacent cities of Berkeley, Emeryville and Piedmont. A short 15-minute drive across the Bay Bridge takes you into Downtown San Francisco.

Highlights of the neighborhood include the Temescal district with its many popular restaurants and local shops. The Emeryville Marina, Bay Street Shopping Center, Old Oakland Shopping District, and Chinatown are nearby and worth checking out (all within 10 min drive). The Lake Merritt districts of Grand Lake and Lake Shore with their many restaurants, shops and the oldest children's amusement park, Fairyland (5 min drive), are also easily accessible.

name: Home in Oakland · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 private bath
neighborhood_overview:
Welcome to East Oakland, the heart of The Town. My neighborhood is home to a diverse population. We are centrally located and minutes from the Oakland Airport and all the major Bay Area attractions. You will be staying in a working-class area. You may hear a loud car passing by or one of Oakland's famous Side Shows in the distance during the day. Down the street and around the corner you will find an unhoused couple that find solace in their vehicle. They are not on my street, or visible from my home, but they are members of this community. While visiting the Bay Area, please extend grace to our unsheltered population.
#TOWNLOVE

Down the street and around the corner you will find an unhoused couple that find solace in their vehicle. They are not on my street, or visible from my home, but they are members of this community. While visiting the Bay Area, please extend grace to our unsheltered population.
#TOWNLOVE

name: Home in Oakland · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
The North Oakland Berkeley Emeryville neighborhood (NOBE) is one of the choice up-and-coming neighborhoods of the East Bay. It has become a much-desired destination, particular for those who move from San Francisco. The NOBE real estate housing mix is varied, from historic bungalows to brand new and modern custom homes.

NOBE is perfect for coffee lovers. Here you’ll find Alchemy Collective Café at Alcatraz and Adeline, Tribu Cafe at San Pablo and 64th and Sweet Adeline at 63rd and Adeline.

There’s a great variety of restaurants in NOBE, like Easy Creole, 44 Restaurant and Bar, Giin Thai Canteen and The Vault Café – all around the intersection of Adeline and Alcatraz. There is Moxy Beer Garden for burgers and beer down on Sacramento and James and the Giant Cupcake is one of the prized additions to the ‘hood. After having lunch, head over for some tasty cupcake fun.

Start on the Emeryville walkway starting anywhere west of San Pablo Avenue. Stop by E-22
host_about:
We are Mike, Bethanie, and our furry companion Niko, and we're thrilled to be your hosts during your stay. 

As avid travelers and adventure enthusiasts, we understand the importance of finding a comfortable and welcoming space that feels like home. With Niko wagging his tail in excitement, we can't wait to share our little slice of paradise with you, ensuring your experience here is unforgettable.

name: Guesthouse in Oakland · *New · 1 bedroom · 4 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Perhaps one of the biggest signposts of being in Montclair and the Oakland Hills is the squiggly (dare we say, hairpin?) roads and scenery re-set from urban to forestry. This wealthy outpost, just off Highway 13, contains some of the most coveted real estate in the Bay Area. You won’t find industrial restaurant décor or mustachioed baristas in this pedestrian-friendly village, exuding a Bavarian mountain town vibe. Montclair also happens to be a terrific launching point into Oakland’s wilderness; some of the East Bay’s best hiking is found in nearby Redwood Regional and Joaquin Miller parks, and other gems like Chabot Space & Science Center are tucked away in the hills.

The inside scoop
On Sundays is the Farmers Market

On Saturdays, $1 gets you a flight of wine—and a dose of goodwill—at Farmstead Cheeses, which donates tasting proceeds to local schools.

neighborhood_overview:
We live in between the Dimond and Laurel Districts in East Oakland. Our neighborhood is diverse and vibrant. We know all of our neighbors by name, and you'll often see kids running around the nearby cul-de-sac, people out walking their dogs. Everyone generally being super friendly and neighborly. That being said, this is an urban environment, so it's best to keep general safety guidelines in mind.

There are two incredible grocery stores within a mile (The Mill & Farmer Joe's), and we are within a mile of a dozen or so restaurants and breweries. Some of our favorites: Jo's Modern Thai and Wawa's (Thai), Degree's Plato & Ghosttown (breweries), Raymond's Nudough (Vietnamese), La Farine (boulangerie) and Sequoia Diner (brekkie). There's also incredible latin cuisine in the nearby Fruitvale neighborhood, and we personally love Obelisco.

The best part of Oakland is that you're close to the hustle and bustle but also super close to some of the best hikes, mountain bikin

name: Rental unit in Oakland · *New · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: This furnished apartment is located in Oakland, California's eighth largest city. It's also one of the most diverse cities in the US, thanks to a steady wave of immigrants from all over the world during the 20th century. You can experience an impressive range of international cuisine in Oakland, and a fun nightlife scene in general. Oakland is known for its professional sports franchises like the Golden State Warriors and the Oakland Raiders, as well as major health care, manufacturing, and tech companies. The city also serves as a transportation hub for the entire San Francisco Bay Area, making it easy to get around Oakland as well as connect to other cities.
host_about:
We’re Blueground, a global proptech company with several thousand move-in-ready apartments in a growing number of major cities around the world. With flexible terms and homes in vibrant, centrally based neighborhoods, you’ll feel at home and free to roam for as long as you want — a month, a year, or longer. 

Each apartment is thoughtfully designed with exclusive furnishings, fully equipped kitchens, and incredible amenities – making every day a five-star experience. From day one, you’ll enjoy high-speed Wi-Fi, premium linens, and smart home entertainment. Plus, access to pools, gyms, and outdoor spaces in select buildings.

Why stress over your apartment? We provide a hassle-free alternative — a consistent, quality guest experience that starts even before you arrive. Because we let you book our most up-to-date apartment listings online, confirm with a click, pay securely, and check in easily. 

Even better? You can enhance your stay with car rentals, grocery delivery, laundry services, and more through our special partnerships. 

During your stay
Upon arrival, you’ll either be greeted personally by a Blueground team member or given self-check-in instructions. The entire apartment is yours! You’ll enjoy reliable support via email, phone, and our Guest App, where you can request everything from a home cleaning to extra towels. 

We’ll share all details upon confirmation of your stay.

neighborhood_overview:
Resting in a valley formed by the Hayward fault, Montclair sits on the western slope of California‘s Oakland Hills. With heavily-forested winding roads and the quaint center of Montclair village, this Oakland neighborhood is the perfect place to stay in the East Bay.

The Oakland neighborhood of Montclair radiates sweetness from the moment you arrive. Reminiscent of a small ski town, Montclair Village is the heart of this Oakland district. Compactly filled with rows of stores, coffee shops and restaurants, people flock to this commercial area at all hours of the day to enjoy its charming atmosphere. Montclair village is only 5 minutes down the hill from the property.

name: Home in Oakland · *New · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Millsmont is almost a secret part of Oakland known mostly to locals. It's located on the hillside to the south of Mills College. (It overlooks but is not part of East Oakland, which is further south and to the west.) You can hear the Mills College bells ring each quarter hour.

Our neighbors include a ferry boat captain, a famous Mission mural painter, digital consultants for political campaigns, and a wellness oriented chiropractor.

Almost all of the buildings on our street are single family, middle class homes ($1M in the Bay Area) occupied by long time residents. These include Asian, Latino, black, and white residents and families - we are the most ethnically diverse zip code in the Bay Area. You'll see them all walking dogs on the street.

There's a wonderful natural foods grocery store about 10 minutes away by car - Farmer Joe's has two locations. Further away, there are many other great purveyors - Berkeley Bowl and Rockridge Market Hall.
